.ddx/beads.jsonl:7:{"acceptance":"1. `TestWorkRetryEscalation_NiflheimEvidence_OnlySemanticFailuresRaiseMinPower` proves only semantic acceptance/review failures can increase requested min power/profile.\n2. Land coordination, repeated pre-claim system warnings, decomposed-parent outcomes, and dirty generated DDx evidence do not raise min power.\n3. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... ./cmd/... -run 'RetryEscalation|Preclaim' -count=1` passes.\n4. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... ./cmd/... -count=1` passes.\n5. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.","closing_commit_sha":"d7b11ad464686e99e8ca75cd7b85479f5ad47507","created_at":"2026-06-08T06:13:59.706294736Z","description":"PROBLEM\nThe worker still treats non-semantic retry classes, including repeated pre-claim system-unready warnings, as if they were the same as acceptance failures. That can raise the requested min power or profile even though a stronger model cannot fix the underlying problem.\n\nROOT CAUSE\n`cli/internal/agent/failclass/failclass.go:103-142` already defines the normative boundary: only `OutcomeGenuineFailure` escalates, while dirty worktree, transport, quota, auth, setup, timeout, and merge-conflict outcomes do not. In the worker loop, however, the retry/escalation decision is not consistently reduced to that typed table before min-power/profile selection, so system warnings and structural failures can still drift into the escalation path.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\n- Wire the retry classifier into the worker path that chooses the next requested min power or profile.\n- Treat repeated pre-claim system-unready warnings as operator attention or same-tier retry, not escalation.\n- Keep decomposed-parent outcomes, land coordination failures, and dirty generated DDx evidence out of the min-power escalation path.\n- Allow only semantic acceptance/review failures to raise min power/profile.\n\nNON-SCOPE\n- Do not change review gating or land reconciliation mechanics in this child.\n- Do not alter the low-level failure-class enum unless the worker path needs the typed mapping.","events_attachment":"ddx-01aa7b18/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-01aa7b18","issue_type":"bug","labels":["adr:024","area:agent","area:execute-bead","area:review","area:workers","incident:niflheim-2026-06-06","kind:bug","kind:reliability","phase:iterate","prevention","severity:critical","spec:FEAT-010","spec:TP-021"],"parent":"ddx-334c0958","priority":0,"queue-rank":2060,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-f9fee664","spec-id":"FEAT-010","status":"closed","title":"agent: keep non-semantic failures from raising min power","updated_at":"2026-06-13T13:58:35.876881985Z"}
.ddx/beads.jsonl:12:{"acceptance":"1. `TestExecuteBeadWorker_NiflheimEvidence_EmptyReviewResultCannotClose` proves a non-skipped success path with `cycle_trace.review_result={}` or an equivalent empty `ReviewResult` cannot close a bead and records `review_error` or operator-attention with a non-empty reason.\n2. `TestExecuteBeadWorker_NiflheimEvidence_NilReviewerRequiresExplicitSkip` updates the current nil-reviewer behavior so `Reviewer: nil` only closes when an explicit durable no-review/skip reason is present; otherwise it fails review gating.\n3. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... ./cmd/... -run 'EmptyReviewResult|NilReviewer' -count=1` passes.\n4. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... ./cmd/... -count=1` passes.\n5. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.","closing_commit_sha":"e11565f34c0395f72aeb7d0c6a60a3a445bd2ae9","created_at":"2026-06-08T06:13:09.618782454Z","description":"PROBLEM\nThe worker can treat a successful cycle as closeable even when `ReviewResult` is empty or the reviewer is nil without an explicit skip reason. That matches the Niflheim success records where `cycle_trace.review_result={}` and nil-reviewer paths still reached close.\n\nROOT CAUSE\n`cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_review.go:168-193` defines `ReviewResult` with all evidence fields optional, so the zero value is indistinguishable from a meaningful review artifact. `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_post_review.go:95-107` skips review whenever `Reviewer` is nil or `NoReview` is set, and `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_review_test.go:799-823` proves the nil-reviewer close path exists. Nothing currently rejects a non-skipped empty review result before close.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\n- Add a guard in the post-review or success path that treats an empty non-skipped `ReviewResult` as a review error or operator-attention event.\n- Require an explicit durable skip reason for `Reviewer: nil` or `NoReview` before close.\n- Add regression coverage for empty review close-blocking and explicit skip behavior.\n\nNON-SCOPE\n- Do not change land coordination, pre-claim intake, or decomposition handling in this child.\n- Do not alter the review model itself beyond the gating invariants needed for these regressions.","events_attachment":"ddx-044cd257/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-044cd257","issue_type":"bug","labels":["adr:024","area:agent","area:execute-bead","area:review","area:workers","incident:niflheim-2026-06-06","kind:bug","kind:reliability","phase:iterate","prevention","severity:critical","spec:FEAT-010","spec:TP-021"],"parent":"ddx-334c0958","priority":0,"queue-rank":2030,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-c27267e6","spec-id":"FEAT-010","status":"closed","title":"agent: reject empty review results before close","updated_at":"2026-06-13T13:58:35.748727362Z","work-no-changes-count":1}
.ddx/beads.jsonl:71:{"acceptance":"1. `TestExecuteBeadResult_NiflheimEvidence_CycleTraceCarriesDecisionAudit` proves result JSON/event bodies include `failure_class`, `retry_action`, `escalation_count`, requested/actual routing facts, review status/verdict or explicit skip reason, and land/reconcile status for the Niflheim scenario families.\n2. The audit data is present for the empty-review, land-failure, decomposed-parent, and pre-claim-warning scenarios that appear in this bead.\n3. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... ./cmd/... -run 'CycleTraceCarriesDecisionAudit' -count=1` passes.\n4. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... ./cmd/... -count=1` passes.\n5. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.","closing_commit_sha":"77e9787a8f5cd70c7247bfa3cdbc43e813140f16","created_at":"2026-06-08T06:14:14.359634106Z","description":"PROBLEM\nThe worker result JSON and event payloads do not yet carry enough typed audit data to explain why a bead closed, retried, escalated, reconciled, or went to operator attention. That makes the Niflheim-style failure families hard to classify after the fact and leaves empty review results looking like success.\n\nROOT CAUSE\n`cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go:154-174` defines `ExecutionCycleTrace`, but its current fields are still sparse and optional, so the result can omit the classification trail the worker used. `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_review.go:168-193` also allows a zero-value `ReviewResult` with no verdict, evidence, or skip reason, which makes the review part of the audit trail ambiguous unless additional gating is added elsewhere.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\n- Extend result serialization and event bodies with `failure_class`, `retry_action`, `escalation_count`, requested/actual routing facts, review status/verdict or explicit skip reason, and land/reconcile status.\n- Ensure the Niflheim scenario families all emit those fields so a reader can tell whether the worker closed, retried, escalated, reconciled, or parked the bead.\n- Keep the audit fields stable and machine-readable so regression tests can assert on them directly.\n\nNON-SCOPE\n- Do not redesign the retry policy in this child.\n- Do not duplicate the land/review gating logic covered by sibling children; this child only makes the decision visible.","events_attachment":"ddx-1865eadc/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-1865eadc","issue_type":"bug","labels":["adr:024","area:agent","area:execute-bead","area:review","area:workers","incident:niflheim-2026-06-06","kind:bug","kind:reliability","phase:iterate","prevention","severity:critical","spec:FEAT-010","spec:TP-021"],"parent":"ddx-334c0958","priority":0,"queue-rank":2070,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-df65d404","spec-id":"FEAT-010","status":"closed","title":"agent: record retry and review decision audit fields","updated_at":"2026-06-13T13:58:35.918863249Z"}
