.ddx/beads.jsonl:105:{"acceptance":"1. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... -run 'TestExecuteBead.*Cleanup|TestCleanupAttemptWorktree' -count=1` passes.\n2. A unit test exists for each of these non-success outcomes asserting WorktreeRemove was called: provider_connectivity, no_evidence_produced, execution_failed, structural_validation_failed, land_conflict, post_run_check_failed.\n3. A unit test asserts the success-path classifier does NOT call WorktreeRemove from the new hook (landing path retains ownership).\n4. A unit test asserts `ddx try --no-merge` preserves the worktree regardless of outcome.\n5. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./... -count=1` passes.\n6. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.","closing_commit_sha":"e979bcd786ff98bd4767596dd1ed2dbe76cddb0c","created_at":"2026-05-29T02:02:14.061932044Z","description":"PROBLEM: When a `ddx try`/`ddx work` attempt fails with any non-success\noutcome (`provider_connectivity`, `no_evidence_produced`, `execution_failed`,\n`structural_validation_failed`, `land_conflict`, `post_run_check_failed`),\nits execute-bead worktree under `~/.cache/ddx/exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-\u003cbead\u003e-\u003cattemptID\u003e/`\nis not removed. Cleanup happens only when a *subsequent attempt of the same bead*\nis launched and `RecoverOrphans` runs as pre-spawn sweep.\n\nOBSERVED 2026-05-28 in niflheim drain: a 6.6 GB worktree\n`.execute-bead-wt-niflheim-07f6f8ff-20260528T164209-f179349f` remained 9+\nhours after its attempt failed with `provider_connectivity` (bragi 502).\nThe bead's retry resolved as `already_satisfied` without spawning a new\nexecute-bead worktree (the AC was already met by partially-landed commits\nfrom the failed attempt), so `RecoverOrphans` was never called for that\nbead — the leak is permanent until another attempt at the same bead runs.\n\nThe user reports seeing this pattern consistently across drains, not just\non the one observed bead.\n\nROOT CAUSE: `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_orchestrator.go:393-411`\ndefines `RecoverOrphans` with the docstring \"the parent's responsibility —\ncall it before spawning new workers so stale worktrees from crashed previous\nattempts do not accumulate.\" The function matches strictly by\n`basenamePrefix := ExecuteBeadWtPrefix + beadID + \"-\"` and is only invoked\non a new-attempt pre-spawn path. Two leak conditions follow:\n\n  (a) Bead's retry succeeds via `already_satisfied` (no new worktree\n      spawned because the AC check resolves before agent invocation).\n      The orphan from the prior failed attempt is never matched.\n  (b) Bead is closed for any reason after a failed attempt and is never\n      re-attempted (most common in real flows — failures often resolve\n      via decomposition into different child beads, never returning to\n      the original).\n\nThe post-attempt outcome classifier at\n`cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go:1966` (Classify worker outcome:\ntask_succeeded / task_failed / task_no_changes / ...) is the natural place\nto call `WorktreeRemove` for non-success classes, but does not.\nThe existing landing path at\n`cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_land.go:1088,1329,1679` calls\n`gitOps.RemoveWorktree` correctly for landing-time temp worktrees, but\nthose are different (per-landing) worktrees, not the per-attempt execute-bead\nworktree under `~/.cache/ddx/exec-wt/`.\n\nPROPOSED FIX: Add an attempt-finalize cleanup hook that runs after outcome\nclassification (around `execute_bead.go:1966-2017`) and removes the\nper-attempt execute-bead worktree when the outcome is anything other than\n`task_succeeded`. Preserve only when:\n  1. The operator explicitly opted in via `ddx try --no-merge` (preserve\n     for inspection regardless of outcome).\n  2. An `executions_mirror.go` write or evidence-capture step requires the\n     worktree to persist past classification (verify by reading the call\n     chain at `execute_bead.go:2069-2114`).\n\nImplementation steps the executing agent should follow:\n  1. Read `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go:1423-2017` to confirm the\n     outcome-classification flow and identify the right post-classify hook\n     point.\n  2. Add a helper `cleanupAttemptWorktree(gitOps, workDir, wtPath, outcome,\n     preserveFlag)` that calls `gitOps.WorktreeRemove(workDir, wtPath)` for\n     non-success outcomes unless `preserveFlag` is set.\n  3. Wire it into the outcome-classification path.\n  4. Add a unit test asserting the cleanup branch for each non-success\n     outcome class, and a negative test confirming success-path keeps the\n     worktree (landing path owns that cleanup).\n  5. Update `RecoverOrphans` docstring to reflect that it's now a\n     belt-and-suspenders sweep, not the primary cleanup path.\n\nNON-SCOPE:\n- Changing `RecoverOrphans` behavior or call sites (keep it; it covers\n  hard-crash cases the new hook can't reach).\n- Adding a periodic background sweeper or `ddx doctor` flag for stale\n  worktrees (potential follow-up).\n- Changing the worktree path under `~/.cache/ddx/exec-wt/`.\n- Changing outcome-classification logic or outcome taxonomy.\n- Adding telemetry/metrics for leak rates.\n\nIN-SCOPE FILES:\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go (add the cleanup hook + helper)\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_test.go or sibling _test file (add\n  cleanup tests for each non-success outcome)\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_orchestrator.go (docstring update on\n  RecoverOrphans only; behavior unchanged)\n\nOUT-OF-SCOPE FILES:\n- execute_bead_land.go — landing-time temp-worktree cleanup is correct\n  and untouched.\n- Any code under cli/cmd/ — no CLI surface change required.\n- docs/ — documentation update is downstream of the spec-evolution bead\n  ddx-828a1b8f (worktree resource isolation) and not required here.","events_attachment":"ddx-274943fc/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-274943fc","issue_type":"bug","labels":["area:agent","area:execution","kind:bug","kind:operability","phase:iterate","spec:FEAT-010"],"needs-human-reason":"consecutive_wedge","needs-human-since":"2026-05-31T05:20:40Z","needs-human-source":"ddx work","needs-human-suggested-action":"investigate the repeated wedge (resolver hang / phase-empty heartbeats) and clear the operator-attention state once resolved","needs-human-summary":"bead wedged on 2 consecutive claims (\u003e= threshold 2; last wedge \"progress_watchdog\"); stopped re-claiming and flagged for operator attention","priority":0,"queue-rank":1240,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-90ab9f5e","spec-id":"FEAT-010","status":"closed","title":"execute-bead: clean up worktree on non-success attempt outcomes (currently leaks on failed-then-retried-as-already_satisfied path)","updated_at":"2026-06-13T13:58:32.524062179Z"}
.ddx/beads.jsonl:109:{"acceptance":"1. ExecuteLoopSpec struct defined in cli/internal/agent/spec.go or cli/internal/agent/executeloop/spec.go. Exported fields include at minimum: ProjectRoot, Harness, Model, Profile, Provider, ModelRef, Effort, LabelFilter, Mode, IdleInterval, NoReview, ReviewHarness, ReviewModel, OpaquePassthrough, MaxCostUSD, RequestTimeout, MinPower, MaxPower, FromRev, SpecVersion. Audit: any field present in cobra extraction (agent_cmd.go:1582-1605) or workers.go:25-49 not in this list is a bug.\n\n2. The unified spec does not contain a PollInterval field, a poll_interval JSON tag, or any public compatibility field for the removed polling flag. New CLI/server/API inputs use Mode plus IdleInterval.\n\n3. parseExecuteLoopSpec(cmd *cobra.Command) (ExecuteLoopSpec, DispatchOptions, error) exists in the new package. Called only from cobra RunE in agent_cmd.go. No parallel cobra-extraction block remains. DispatchOptions holds control-plane flags (--local, --json) and is not persisted to spec.json.\n\n4. parseExecuteLoopSpec maps --once to Mode=once, maps --watch to Mode=watch, defaults to Mode=drain, maps --idle-interval to IdleInterval only for Mode=watch, and returns a usage error when --idle-interval is provided without --watch.\n\n5. Spec.Validate() and Spec.ApplyDefaults() methods exist. Lifecycle enforced: (a) client calls Validate() before HTTP submit or inline dispatch; (b) server handleStartExecuteLoopWorker calls ApplyDefaults() then Validate() after decode, before StartExecuteLoop; (c) spec.json on disk is fully resolved (ApplyDefaults already ran at write time).\n\n6. handleStartExecuteLoopWorker (cli/internal/server/server.go:2390) decodes directly into ExecuteLoopSpec; the anonymous request struct (currently lines 2395-2409) is deleted. Mode, IdleInterval, OpaquePassthrough, MaxCostUSD, RequestTimeout, MinPower, MaxPower, and FromRev survive the REST round-trip.\n\n7. graphql_adapters.go anonymous request struct (lines 63-76) and its parallel StartExecuteLoop literal (lines 127-141) are deleted. GraphQL dispatch goes through the same server-side ApplyDefaults + Validate + StartExecuteLoop as the REST handler.\n\n8. ExecuteLoopWorkerSpec in cli/internal/server/workers.go:25-49 is replaced by or aliased to ExecuteLoopSpec. spec.json files written by StartExecuteLoop use the unified struct and emit Mode plus IdleInterval.\n\n9. runWorker (cli/internal/server/workers.go:658) consumes spec.MaxCostUSD as the cost-cap ceiling, with escalation.DefaultMaxCostUSD fallback when zero. No hardcoded DefaultMaxCostUSD reference outside the fallback case.\n\n10. OpaquePassthrough: server-submitted spec with OpaquePassthrough=true skips both validation gates - workers.go:357-361 (StartExecuteLoop pre-flight) and the ValidateForExecuteLoopViaService branch inside runWorker. TestStartExecuteLoop_OpaquePassthrough_SkipsValidation asserts that StartExecuteLoop with OpaquePassthrough=true does not call ValidateForExecuteLoopViaService and returns a WorkerRecord without error even when the harness name is unresolvable.\n\n11. Reflection round-trip test: TestExecuteLoopSpec_RoundTripsAllFields_Reflection in cli/internal/agent/spec_test.go or executeloop sub-package. Uses reflect to iterate exported fields of ExecuteLoopSpec; for each field sets a non-zero sentinel value; marshals to JSON; unmarshals; asserts equality. Test fails if any exported field has a zero-value sentinel after unmarshal. A future added field automatically falls under coverage.\n\n12. Backward compatibility for disk only: existing spec.json files in .ddx/workers/ load without error. Files containing unknown legacy fields are tolerated and ignored by json.Unmarshal default behavior. Do not enable json.Decoder.DisallowUnknownFields for disk reads.\n\n13. Forward compatibility: SpecVersion int field present. Server returns HTTP 400 with a capability description when incoming SpecVersion \u003e server-supported version. SpecVersion==0 (unset) is treated as the current version. TestHandleStartExecuteLoopWorker_HighSpecVersion_Returns400 covers this.\n\n14. Regression: inline execution path behavior is unchanged except for the explicit once/drain/watch mapping. Existing tests that cover the inline path pass without modification.\n\n15. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./cmd/... ./internal/agent/... ./internal/server/... green.\n\n16. lefthook run pre-commit passes.","created_at":"2026-05-02T20:54:27.571475194Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ddx-29058e2a","depends_on_id":"ddx-1a9cc01f","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-06T21:36:45Z"},{"issue_id":"ddx-29058e2a","depends_on_id":"ddx-76cf71f4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-06T21:36:46Z"},{"issue_id":"ddx-29058e2a","depends_on_id":"ddx-89a9c305","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-06T21:36:47Z"},{"issue_id":"ddx-29058e2a","depends_on_id":"ddx-16722d4e","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-06T21:36:48Z"}],"description":"PROBLEM\nExecuteLoopSpec fields are declared in parallel structs across three independent code sites. When a flag or worker mode is added to cobra, the developer must also update the REST handler request struct in server.go and the GraphQL adapter request struct in graphql_adapters.go; missing one silently drops the field at runtime. The new work-loop contract requires one vocabulary across CLI parsing, worker persistence, REST, and GraphQL: mode plus idle_interval, with no public compatibility alias for the removed polling flag.\n\nROOT CAUSE\nEach work field traverses six independent declaration points with no compile-time linkage:\n\n1. cobra flag extraction plus local vars: cli/cmd/agent_cmd.go:1582-1605 extracts fromRev, harness, model, profile, provider, modelRef, effort, once/watch mode, idleInterval, noReview, reviewHarness, reviewModel, maxCostUSD, requestTimeout, minPower, and maxPower as naked locals.\n\n2. positional-param pass-down: cli/cmd/agent_cmd.go:1744-1773 closes over these locals and assembles config.CLIOverrides by hand; no single struct groups them.\n\n3. ExecuteLoopWorkerSpec definition: cli/internal/server/workers.go:25-49 is hand-maintained in parallel with cobra and has historically missed fields.\n\n4. handleStartExecuteLoopWorker request struct: cli/internal/server/server.go:2395-2409 is a separate anonymous struct, so newly added fields can be silently lost for server-spawned workers.\n\n5. StartExecuteLoop literal: cli/internal/server/server.go:2441-2455 plus cli/internal/server/workers.go:345-361 hand-assembles the worker spec; any field absent in step 4 cannot appear here.\n\n6. GraphQL adapter request struct plus StartExecuteLoop literal: cli/internal/server/graphql_adapters.go:63-76 plus 127-141 is a third parallel declaration; fixes to REST can leave GraphQL broken.\n\nThe consumer (cli/internal/server/workers.go:658-926 runWorker) reads MaxCostUSD from escalation.DefaultMaxCostUSD hardcoded (line ~753) instead of spec.MaxCostUSD because the field was never plumbed through. OpaquePassthrough has two validation skip gates that must both fire (workers.go:357-361 and the ValidateForExecuteLoopViaService branch in runWorker).\n\nPROPOSED FIX\n- cli/internal/agent/spec.go or cli/internal/agent/executeloop/spec.go: define ExecuteLoopSpec with all fields currently spread across the six layers. Fields: ProjectRoot, Harness, Model, Profile, Provider, ModelRef, Effort, LabelFilter, Mode, IdleInterval, NoReview, ReviewHarness, ReviewModel, OpaquePassthrough, MaxCostUSD, RequestTimeout, MinPower, MaxPower, FromRev, SpecVersion int. JSON tags drive both REST wire format and disk persistence.\n- Mode is the canonical once/drain/watch selector. CLI --once maps to Mode=once. CLI --watch maps to Mode=watch. Default is Mode=drain.\n- IdleInterval is meaningful only for Mode=watch. --idle-interval without --watch is a usage error in the cobra layer and must not be represented as a separate polling mode in the persisted spec.\n- Do not add, accept, document, or emit a public compatibility alias for the removed polling flag. Historical worker records may be read best-effort as unknown/legacy input, but new CLI/server/API inputs use Mode plus IdleInterval.\n- Add Spec.Validate() and Spec.ApplyDefaults(). Add parseExecuteLoopSpec(cmd *cobra.Command) (ExecuteLoopSpec, DispatchOptions, error) as the single cobra-to-spec conversion.\n- cli/cmd/agent_cmd.go:1582-1605: replace naked-local extraction with parseExecuteLoopSpec. Remove positional-param closure pattern; pass spec by value.\n- cli/internal/server/workers.go:25-49: replace ExecuteLoopWorkerSpec with (or alias to) ExecuteLoopSpec from the new package. Delete the parallel struct.\n- cli/internal/server/server.go:2395-2409: delete the anonymous request struct in handleStartExecuteLoopWorker; decode directly into ExecuteLoopSpec. Call ApplyDefaults() then Validate() before StartExecuteLoop.\n- cli/internal/server/graphql_adapters.go:63-76 plus 127-141: delete the parallel anonymous struct and parallel StartExecuteLoop literal; route through the same server-side ApplyDefaults + Validate + StartExecuteLoop as REST.\n- cli/internal/server/workers.go:~753: replace hardcoded escalation.DefaultMaxCostUSD with spec.MaxCostUSD, with DefaultMaxCostUSD as fallback when zero.\n- cli/internal/agent/spec_test.go or cli/internal/agent/executeloop/spec_test.go: TestExecuteLoopSpec_RoundTripsAllFields_Reflection uses reflect over exported fields; sets non-zero value per field; marshals; unmarshals; asserts round-trip. New field = automatic coverage.\n\nNON-SCOPE\n- ddx-eccc6efb (ADR-022 step 7) owns replacing runWorker with exec ddx work; this bead does not change the subprocess vs in-process dispatch decision.\n- Other commands (ddx agent run, ddx try, MCP agent dispatch) may have the same smell; covered by sister bead ddx-fb290074.\n- Reshaping LabelFilter from string to []string is owned by ddx-9d55601f; keep LabelFilter as string.\n\nSEQUENCING\nddx-29058e2a (this bead) vs ddx-eccc6efb (ADR-022 step 7 - server-spawn migration to exec ddx work): lands independently and before ddx-eccc6efb. ADR-022 says ddx-29058e2a remains valuable as worker-side struct unification (cobra to in-process flow) and should land independently. When ddx-eccc6efb lands later, it will delete ExecuteLoopWorkerSpec from workers.go as part of the exec migration; the unified ExecuteLoopSpec should already live in the durable agent package. If ddx-eccc6efb lands first, the scope of this bead narrows to the cobra and worker-facing layers that still exist.","events":[{"actor":"ddx","body":"{\"resolved_provider\":\"claude\",\"fallback_chain\":[],\"requested_harness\":\"claude\"}","created_at":"2026-05-02T20:54:37.989096911Z","kind":"routing","source":"ddx agent execute-bead","summary":"provider=claude"},{"actor":"ddx","body":"exit status 1\nresult_rev=dd174d4ac0529ac46a42985281f3113fe54efa51\nbase_rev=dd174d4ac0529ac46a42985281f3113fe54efa51\nretry_after=2026-05-03T02:54:38Z","created_at":"2026-05-02T20:54:38.513521822Z","kind":"execute-bead","source":"ddx agent work","summary":"execution_failed"},{"actor":"ddx","body":"{\"resolved_provider\":\"claude\",\"fallback_chain\":[]}","created_at":"2026-05-03T03:09:52.257218554Z","kind":"routing","source":"ddx agent execute-bead","summary":"provider=claude"},{"actor":"ddx","body":"{\"attempt_id\":\"20260503T025809-45a220f7\",\"harness\":\"claude\",\"input_tokens\":0,\"output_tokens\":0,\"total_tokens\":0,\"cost_usd\":2.81355875,\"duration_ms\":689043,\"exit_code\":1}","created_at":"2026-05-03T03:09:52.275641898Z","kind":"cost","source":"ddx agent execute-bead","summary":"tokens=0 cost_usd=2.8136"},{"actor":"erik","body":"exit status 1\nresult_rev=e24ac3d8e7fe88b3f56cd9242cb058b2e754c4d7\nbase_rev=e24ac3d8e7fe88b3f56cd9242cb058b2e754c4d7\nretry_after=2026-05-03T09:09:52Z","created_at":"2026-05-03T03:09:52.392741346Z","kind":"execute-bead","source":"ddx agent work","summary":"execution_failed"},{"actor":"ddx","body":"{\"detail\":\"routing preflight rejected (harness=codex