 the current nil-reviewer behavior so `Reviewer: nil` only closes when an explicit durable no-review/skip reason is present; otherwise it fails review gating.\",\"coverage\":\"Child 'Enforce execute-bead review evidence before success close' AC2.\"},{\"parent_ac\":\"4. `TestExecuteBeadLoop_NiflheimEvidence_LandCoordinationFailureDoesNotRerunImplementation` simulates both observed details (`cannot lock ref refs/heads/main` after a candidate/merge is already landed, and `landing worktree has staged changes after waiting 2s`) and asserts the action is reconcile/retry-land/operator-attention, not a fresh implementation run and not model escalation.\",\"coverage\":\"Child 'Classify land coordination failures without implementation reruns' AC1 and AC2.\"},{\"parent_ac\":\"5. `TestExecuteBeadLoop_NiflheimEvidence_DecomposedParentIsExecutionIneligible` simulates `mixed_commit_and_no_changes_rationale` with `orchestrator_action: decompose`, child bead IDs, and `outcome_reason=decomposed`; it asserts the parent is marked execution-ineligible/proposed or dependency-waiting according to policy and that no further implementation attempt or min-power escalation is scheduled.\",\"coverage\":\"Child 'Mark decomposed parent beads execution-ineligible before retry' AC1 and AC2.\"},{\"parent_ac\":\"6. `TestWorkRetryEscalation_NiflheimEvidence_OnlySemanticFailuresRaiseMinPower` proves only semantic acceptance/review failures can increase requested min power/profile. Land coordination, repeated pre-claim system warnings, decomposed-parent outcomes, and dirty generated DDx evidence must not raise min power.\",\"coverage\":\"Child 'Classify repeated pre-claim system warnings as operator-visible worker state' AC2 carries the full cross-scenario test; child 'Classify land coordination failures without implementation reruns' AC2 covers land coordination; child 'Mark decomposed parent beads execution-ineligible before retry' AC2 covers decomposed parent.\"},{\"parent_ac\":\"7. `TestExecuteBeadResult_NiflheimEvidence_CycleTraceCarriesDecisionAudit` proves result JSON/event bodies include `failure_class`, `retry_action`, `escalation_count`, requested/actual routing facts, review status/verdict or explicit skip reason, and land/reconcile status for the Niflheim scenario families.\",\"coverage\":\"Child 'Enforce execute-bead review evidence before success close' AC3 covers review audit; child 'Classify land coordination failures without implementation reruns' AC3 covers land/reconcile audit; child 'Mark decomposed parent beads execution-ineligible before retry' AC3 covers decomposed-parent audit; child 'Classify repeated pre-claim system warnings as operator-visible worker state' AC3 covers pre-claim audit.\"},{\"parent_ac\":\"8. Existing related behavior from `ddx-2965925e`, `ddx-b2846610`, and `ddx-d67f124e` remains covered; this bead either reuses their helpers or waits for those dependencies, and does not add duplicate low-level implementations.\",\"coverage\":\"Child 'Classify land coordination failures without implementation reruns' AC4 preserves `ddx-2965925e` and `ddx-b2846610`; child 'Classify repeated pre-claim system warnings as operator-visible worker state' AC4 preserves `ddx-d67f124e`; every child description preserves all three dependency IDs and the parent non-scope constraints.\"},{\"parent_ac\":\"9. `cd cli \\u0026\\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... ./cmd/... -run 'NiflheimEvidence|EmptyReviewResult|NilReviewer|LandCoordination|DecomposedParent|RetryEscalation|CycleTraceCarriesDecisionAudit' -count=1` passes.\",\"coverage\":\"Covered as child-specific focused gates: review child AC4, land child AC5, decomposed-parent child AC5, pre-claim/escalation child AC5.\"},{\"parent_ac\":\"10. `cd cli \\u0026\\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... ./cmd/... -count=1` passes.\",\"coverage\":\"Review child AC5, land child AC6, decomposed-parent child AC6, pre-claim/escalation child AC6.\"},{\"parent_ac\":\"11. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.\",\"coverage\":\"Review child AC6, land child AC7, decomposed-parent child AC7, pre-claim/escalation child AC7.\"}],\"child_ids\":[\"ddx-cdd1a0b2\",\"ddx-bced4e39\",\"ddx-d2725150\",\"ddx-eea2dfca\"],\"rationale\":\"The parent bead mixes four independently testable failure families: review evidence gating, land coordination classification, decomposed-parent execution eligibility, and repeated pre-claim system warnings/retry escalation. Splitting on those boundaries keeps each child within one worker decision path while preserving the same governing references, parent non-scope constraints, dependency IDs, Niflheim incident facts, audit-field requirements, go test gates, and pre-commit gate. The only deliberately cross-scenario assertion is the min-power escalation rule, assigned to the pre-claim/escalation child with supporting focused assertions in the land and decomposed-parent children so no child needs to depend on another child.\"}","created_at":"2026-06-08T06:18:28.973348717Z","kind":"triage-decomposed","source":"ddx work","summary":"decomposed into ddx-cdd1a0b2, ddx-bced4e39, ddx-d2725150, ddx-eea2dfca"}],"execution-eligible":false,"id":"ddx-334c0958","issue_type":"bug","labels":["adr:024","area:agent","area:execute-bead","area:review","area:workers","incident:niflheim-2026-06-06","kind:bug","kind:reliability","phase:iterate","prevention","severity:critical","spec:FEAT-010","spec:TP-021"],"notes":"decomposed into ddx-044cd257, ddx-3a6f1ad6, ddx-d4817c9b, ddx-01aa7b18, ddx-1865eadc","parent":"ddx-3106674f","priority":0,"queue-rank":1850,"schema_version":1,"spec-id":"FEAT-010","status":"open","title":"execute-bead worker: gate success on review evidence and classify Niflheim retry failures","updated_at":"2026-06-13T13:58:35.074272895Z","work-no-changes-count":1}
