ge with unrelated concerns. The ddx try CLI command named in FEAT-010 does not exist (cli/cmd/try.go absent).\n\nPROPOSED FIX\n  Rename per the following table (no behavior change):\n    cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go             -\u003e cli/internal/agent/try/attempt.go (already exists; merge or verify)\n    cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_orchestrator.go -\u003e cli/internal/agent/try/land.go\n    cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_land.go         -\u003e cli/internal/agent/try/coordinator.go\n    cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_review.go       -\u003e cli/internal/agent/try/review.go\n    cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_review_triage.go -\u003e cli/internal/agent/try/review_triage.go\n    cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_status.go       -\u003e cli/internal/agent/try/disposition.go\n    cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go         -\u003e cli/internal/agent/work/drain.go\n    cli/internal/agent/executions_mirror.go         -\u003e cli/internal/agent/try/mirror.go\n\n  Rename identifiers: ExecuteBeadWorker -\u003e work.Worker, ExecuteBeadWorker.Run -\u003e work.Worker.Drain, ExecuteBead -\u003e try.Attempt (FEAT-006 + FEAT-010).\n\n  Add cli/cmd/try.go with cobra command \"ddx try \u003cbead-id\u003e\" invoking try.Attempt directly (FEAT-010 surface).\n\n  Update FEAT-006 and FEAT-010 spec docs to reflect new package paths. Keep ExecuteBead* shims as typedefs; deletion is C14.\n\nNON-SCOPE\n  - Behavior changes to the drain loop or attempt logic.\n  - Deletion of ExecuteBead* typedefs (C14).\n  - ddx-dc157075 file-path reference migration if that bead has not yet landed.\n\nINTERSECTIONS\n- P2: file and identifier names should reflect the subsystem boundary and keep responsibilities separated.\n- P5: ddx try as a first-class CLI surface makes the worker/attempt state easier for operators to see.\n- P7: the refactor aligns names and prompt surface with the bead-as-prompt contract.","events":[{"actor":"","body":"[{\"ac\":1,\"text\":\"All file renames in the table