.ddx/beads.jsonl:161:{"acceptance":"1. `TestExecuteBeadLoop_NiflheimEvidence_LandCoordinationFailureDoesNotRerunImplementation` simulates both observed details (`cannot lock ref refs/heads/main` after a candidate/merge is already landed, and `landing worktree has staged changes after waiting 2s`) and asserts the action is reconcile/retry-land/operator-attention, not a fresh implementation run and not model escalation.\n2. The regression shows the worker preserves or reconciles land state instead of rerunning implementation when the land result is already effectively landed or blocked by dirty staged evidence.\n3. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... ./cmd/... -run 'LandCoordination' -count=1` passes.\n4. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... ./cmd/... -count=1` passes.\n5. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.","closing_commit_sha":"f11e2988d00ff1d9376a839b6bf450969e4c303a","created_at":"2026-06-08T06:13:37.906342882Z","description":"PROBLEM\nLanding failures that are really ref-lock, already-landed, or staged-evidence coordination issues still look like ordinary implementation failures to the worker. That causes fresh implementation reruns and the wrong retry lane instead of reconciliation or operator attention.\n\nROOT CAUSE\n`cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_orchestrator.go:292-312` wraps every `LandingAdvancer` error as a generic `land advancer` failure, which loses whether the candidate was already landed, whether `refs/heads/main` could not be locked, or whether the landing worktree was dirty. `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_report_test.go:57-62` only proves the current detail string records land failure; it does not distinguish the coordination class from implementation failure.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\n- Split land/ref/index/evidence-staging failures into explicit retry actions: reconcile, retry-land, or operator-attention.\n- If the candidate commit or merge is already landed or is an ancestor of the target, reconcile and continue without rerunning implementation.\n- If the landing worktree has staged generated evidence or DDx metadata, preserve or retry the land/evidence step according to local policy rather than escalating the model.\n\nNON-SCOPE\n- Do not change review gating, decomposition detection, or power escalation policy in this child.\n- Do not reimplement low-level tracker/index contention fixes owned by sibling work.","events_attachment":"ddx-3a6f1ad6/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-3a6f1ad6","issue_type":"bug","labels":["adr:024","area:agent","area:execute-bead","area:review","area:workers","incident:niflheim-2026-06-06","kind:bug","kind:reliability","phase:iterate","prevention","severity:critical","spec:FEAT-010","spec:TP-021"],"parent":"ddx-334c0958","priority":0,"queue-rank":2040,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-c8a3ce86","spec-id":"FEAT-010","status":"closed","title":"agent: classify land coordination failures as reconciliation","updated_at":"2026-06-13T13:58:35.789249002Z"}
.ddx/beads.jsonl:164:{"acceptance":"1. TestServiceExecuteErrorClassifiesProviderConfigFailures uses a fake Fizeau service returning representative pre-dispatch errors for auth missing, model unavailable, provider unavailable, and endpoint timeout; each produces a typed ExecuteBeadReport outcome_reason/disruption_reason instead of generic execution_failed.\n2. TestServiceFinalFailureClassifiesProviderRouteHealth uses fake final events for provider timeout, quota/rate-limit, model unavailable, and harness unavailable; each is normalized into the provider failure taxonomy with retryable vs hard-pin semantics preserved.\n3. TestUnpinnedWorkerFallsBackAfterTypedProviderFailure proves a zero-config/unpinned worker records failed-route evidence and asks Fizeau for a different eligible route or higher floor rather than parking the bead on the first provider failure.\n4. TestPinnedWorkerReportsHardPinExhaustedWithoutWidening proves --harness/--provider/--model pins do not get silently removed, and the report names the typed provider failure plus operator remediation.\n5. TestProviderFailureEvidenceNamesFallbackDecision proves the bead/run evidence includes requested constraints, resolved route if any, typed failure, retryability, fallback_attempted, and fallback_stop_reason.\n6. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./cmd/... ./internal/agent/... -run 'TestServiceExecuteErrorClassifiesProviderConfigFailures|TestServiceFinalFailureClassifiesProviderRouteHealth|TestUnpinnedWorkerFallsBackAfterTypedProviderFailure|TestPinnedWorkerReportsHardPinExhaustedWithoutWidening|TestProviderFailureEvidenceNamesFallbackDecision' passes.\n7. lefthook run pre-commit passes.","closing_commit_sha":"67ae82b42b3b7f7efdf9edb03e37c701fae3ae45","created_at":"2026-06-13T17:35:34.801862687Z","description":"PROBLEM\nDDx/FIZ worker failures can still surface as underspecified execution failures when provider availability, model availability, credentials, endpoint reachability, or harness configuration differs across machines. DDx is the abstraction that should let unattended workers continue through provider variance; a generic provider failure that gives no typed cause, no fallback action, and no durable route-health evidence is a product bug.\n\nROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\ncli/internal/agent/service_run.go:287-290 returns pre-dispatch Fizeau Execute errors as a generic `agent: execute: %w`, leaving the execute loop without a typed provider/model/configuration failure contract.\ncli/internal/agent/service_run.go:332-376 copies final service error text into Result.Error/ExitCode, but downstream classification still depends on free-text heuristics rather than a required typed route-health outcome for provider unavailable, model unavailable, auth missing, quota/rate limit, endpoint timeout, or harness misconfiguration.\ncli/cmd/execute_loop_shared.go:516-544 and :588-612 contain the unpinned route-exclusion/escalation path, but that path only works when the failure is already recognized as provider_connectivity/no_viable_provider; untyped provider/configuration failures can stop or preserve the bead without proving fallback was attempted or intentionally impossible.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\n- Define a typed provider failure taxonomy at the DDx/Fizeau boundary: provider_connectivity, provider_auth, provider_rate_limit, provider_quota, provider_model_unavailable, provider_harness_unavailable, provider_config_invalid, no_viable_provider, and unknown_provider_failure.\n- Normalize both pre-dispatch Execute errors and final failed events into that taxonomy before ExecuteBeadReport construction.\n- For unpinned workers, convert retryable provider/model/harness availability failures into route-health evidence and continue fallback/escalation without parking the bead.\n- For explicit operator pins, fail loudly with a typed hard-pin exhausted/operator-action report that names the pin and available remediation, without silently widening pins.\n- Persist durable evidence on the bead/run showing requested constraints, resolved route if any, typed failure, retryability, whether fallback was attempted, and why fallback stopped.\n\nNON-SCOPE\nDo not move concrete route selection into DDx; Fizeau still owns routing, aliases, model discovery, and provider catalog behavior. Do not remove explicit operator pins. Do not call real providers in tests.","events_attachment":"ddx-3b721804/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-3b721804","issue_type":"bug","labels":["phase:build","area:agent","area:work","area:routing","kind:bug","kind:reliability","severity:critical","plan:server-managed-workers"],"parent":"ddx-9d1af129","priority":0,"queue-rank":"-120","schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-9a2b4976","spec-id":"IP-2026-06-13-server-managed-workers","status":"closed","title":"agent: type provider failures and enforce fallback semantics","updated_at":"2026-06-13T18:38:23.850216294Z"}
.ddx/beads.jsonl:179:{"created_at":"2026-05-16T04:22:58.739404633Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ddx-3fd19af1","depends_on_id":"ddx-3e8ba14b","type":"depends_on","created_at":"2026-06-06T02:27:26Z"},{"issue_id":"ddx-3fd19af1","depends_on_id":"ddx-38801c65","type":"depends_on","created_at":"2026-06-06T02:27:26Z"}],"description":"PROBLEM\nThe foundation bead for TD-027 split the bead storage migration into caller-facing and package-local slices, but the current `ddx-464feba2` child still bundles the Store API migration together with a repo-wide caller sweep. The local `cli/internal/bead` package work is still a valid, self-contained slice: `cli/internal/bead/backend.go` already declares ctx-first interfaces, while `cli/internal/bead/store.go` still exposes the legacy zero-arg methods (`Init`, `ReadAll`, `Get`, `Create`, `Update`, `Close`, `GenID`).\n\nROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\n- `cli/internal/bead/backend.go:74-100` declares the ctx-first foundation interfaces.\n- `cli/internal/bead/store.go:140-1181` still exposes the legacy no-ctx Store methods.\n- `ddx-464feba2` was blocked because the broader caller migration exceeds that child slice.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\nUpdate only the core bead package surface so the Store methods in `cli/internal/bead/store.go` accept `ctx context.Context` as first parameter for the foundational non-event methods, and keep the verification local to `cli/internal/bead/...`. Do not touch the external caller sweep in this bead. Update or add the store/package tests needed to prove the local API still behaves correctly after the signature change.\n\nNON-SCOPE\n- Caller migration in `cli/cmd`, `cli/internal/agent`, `cli/internal/server`, `cli/internal/escalation`, and metrics packages.\n- Event method ctx threading (`AppendEvent`, `Events`, `EventsByKind`).\n- Removing workflow helper methods beyond the foundational signatures this bead changes.\n\nACCEPTANCE\n1. The foundational Store methods in `cli/internal/bead/store.go` take `ctx context.Context` first: `Init`, `ReadAll`, `ReadAllFiltered`, `Get`, `GetWithArchive`, `Create`, `Update`, `Close`, and `GenID`.\n2. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/bead/...` passes.\n3. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.\n4. Any tests added or updated in `cli/internal/bead/` are named and deterministic, with no caller-package changes in this bead.","events":[{"actor":"ddx","body":"{\"resolved_provider\":\"claude\",\"resolved_model\":\"opus\",\"fallback_chain\":[]}","created_at":"2026-05-16T04:51:05.315282637Z","kind":"routing","source":"legacy agent execute-bead","summary":"provider=claude model=opus"},{"actor":"ddx","body":"{\"attempt_id\":\"20260516T043007-7ac09885\",\"harness\":\"claude\",\"model\":\"opus\",\"input_tokens\":53,\"output_tokens\":26527,\"total_tokens\":26580,\"cost_usd\":3.1411672499999996,\"duration_ms\":1251919,\"exit_code\":0}","created_at":"2026-05-16T04:51:05.356780024Z","kind":"cost","source":"legacy agent execute-bead","summary":"tokens=26580 cost_usd=3.1412 model=opus"},{"actor":"ddx","body":"{\"actual_harness\":\"claude\",\"actual_model\":\"opus\",\"actual_power\":0,\"actual_provider\":\"\",\"attempt_id\":\"20260516T043007-7ac09885\",\"bead_id\":\"ddx-3fd19af1\",\"estimated_difficulty\":\"medium\",\"rejected_route_pins\":null,\"requested_power_class\":\"standard\",\"requested_profile\":\"default\",\"routing_intent_degraded\":false,\"routing_intent_note\":\"\",\"routing_intent_source\":\"readiness\"}","created_at":"2026-05-16T04:51:05.749843329Z","kind":"execution-routing-intent","source":"ddx work","summary":"source=readiness difficulty=medium powerClass=standard model=opus harness=claude"},{"actor":"erik","body":"status=proposed\nreason=bead AC1+AC3 contradict the explicit non-scope; needs operator re-scoping Findings (worktree base-rev 86de1c4af, .ddx/executions/20260516T043007-7ac09885): 1. Current state of the foundational Store methods (cli/internal/bead/store.go): Init(args ...any) error                                  // line 149 GenID(args ...any) (string, error)                       // line 167 ReadAll(args ...any) ([]Bead, error)                     // line 182 ReadAllFiltered(args ...any) ([]Bead, error)             // line 224 Create(args ...any) error                                // line 518 Get(args ...any) (*Bead, error)                          // line 598 Update(args ...any) error                                // line 627 Close(args ...any) error                                 // line 1426 And in archive.go: GetWithArchive(id string) (*Bead, error)                 // line 172 Each variadic method extracts ctx via storeCallContext(args) and accepts either `s.Init()` or `s.Init(context.Background())` today. 2. AC1 requires these methods to take `ctx context.Context` as a typed first parameter (matching the BeadEventReader / BeadQueries shape already in cli/internal/bead/backend.go:91-114). Any concrete signature satisfying AC1 — `Init(ctx context.Context) error`, `Init(ctx context.Context, args ...any) error`, etc. — rejects the current zero-arg `s.Init()` callsites that exist in external packages. 3. The bead's PROPOSED FIX and NON-SCOPE explicitly forbid touching external callers (\"Do not touch the external caller sweep in this bead\"; \"NON-SCOPE: Caller migration in cli/cmd, cli/internal/agent, cli/internal/server, cli/internal/escalation, and metrics packages.\") and AC4 requires \"no caller-package changes in this bead.\" 4. AC3 requires `lefthook run pre-commit` to pass, which runs `go build -buildvcs=false -v ./...` from cli/ (lefthook.yml:122-129). That build covers every package in the module, including all the external caller packages NON-SCOPE forbids touching. 5. Concrete external breakage if AC1 is implemented today (`grep -rE '\\b(store|s)\\.(Init|Create|Update|Get|Close|ReadAll|GenID|GetWithArchive|ReadAllFiltered)\\(' cli/ --include='*.go'`): - 174 Go files reference these Store methods. - 73 distinct files outside cli/internal/bead/ use the zero-arg `store.Init()` form (e.g. cli/cmd/ac_test.go:37, cli/cmd/bead_human_test.go:20, cli/internal/agent/..., cli/internal/server/...). - Production-code stragglers without ctx exist too: cli/cmd/bead.go:414  s.GetWithArchive(args[0]) cli/cmd/bead.go:1281 s.Close(id) cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:4485 store.Get(id) cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:4811 store.Update(beadID, ...) `go build ./...` and the lefthook go-build hook will fail at every one of those callsites the instant Init/Get/Update/Close/ReadAll/GenID/ GetWithArchive/ReadAllFiltered become non-variadic ctx-first. There is no signature shape that satisfies AC1 while preserving all current call patterns (Go does not allow same-name method overloads on a single receiver type). 6. Step 0 size envelope is also exceeded for the only resolution that preserves AC1+AC3: the necessary mechanical caller sweep crosses ~170 files in five packages (cmd, internal/agent, internal/server, internal/attemptmetrics, internal/agentmetrics) — well past the \"~500 lines across ~5+ files in unrelated packages\" guardrail. That is exactly the sweep that NON-SCOPE excludes, and the parent split (TD-027 / ddx-464feba2) was rejected for the same reason. Operator action requested: Re-scope this bead to one of: (a) Add the caller-package migration to scope (delete the NON-SCOPE block and AC4's \"no caller-package changes\"). This becomes the original TD-027 sweep that previously failed as too large; if pursued, expect a multi-file diff across cli/cmd, cli/internal/agent, cli/internal/server, cli/internal/attemptmetrics, cli/internal/agentmetrics. (b) Replace AC3 with a narrower verification (e.g. \"go test ./internal/bead/... and go vet ./internal/bead/... pass\"), and explicitly accept that `go build ./...` and lefthook pre-commit will be red until follow-up caller-migration beads land. The follow-up beads would then re-establish AC3 once the sweep is complete. (c) Replace AC1 with an additive shape that does not rename or retype the existing variadic methods — e.g. \"add new ctx-first Store methods with distinct names (InitCtx / GetCtx / …) so the legacy variadic surface stays in place during the migration\", then a follow-up bead deletes the variadic methods after the caller sweep finishes. This satisfies the spirit of TD-027 (introducing the typed ctx-first surface in the bead package first) without breaking the build outside the package. No code changes were made on this attempt. Request was triaged strictly against the bead body — no /tmp scratch files, no work outside the worktree.\nsuggested_action=review and accept, split, block, or cancel this proposed work","created_at":"2026-05-16T04:51:05.820176946Z","kind":"no_changes_operator_required","source":"ddx work","summary":"no_changes_operator_required"},{"actor":"erik","body":"no_changes\npowerClass=standard\nrationale: status: proposed\nreason: bead AC1+AC3 contradict the explicit non-scope; needs operator re-scoping\n\nFindings (worktree base-rev 86de1c4af, .ddx/executions/20260516T043007-7ac09885):\n\n1. Current state of the foundational Store methods (cli/internal/bead/store.go):\n     Init(args ...any) error                                  // line 149\n     GenID(args ...any) (string, error)                       // line 167\n     ReadAll(args ...any) ([]Bead, error)                     // line 182\n     ReadAllFiltered(args ...any) ([]Bead, error)             // line 224\n     Create(args ...any) error                                // line 518\n     Get(args ...any) (*Bead, error)                          // line 598\n     Update(args ...any) error                                // line 627\n     Close(args ...any) error                                 // line 1426\n   And in archive.go:\n     GetWithArchive(id string) (*Bead, error)                 // line 172\n   Each variadic method extracts ctx via storeCallContext(args) and accepts\n   either `s.Init()` or `s.Init(context.Background())` today.\n\n2. AC1 requires these methods to take `ctx context.Context` as a typed first\n   parameter (matching the BeadEventReader / BeadQueries shape already in\n   cli/internal/bead/backend.go:91-114). Any concrete signature satisfying\n   AC1 — `Init(ctx context.Context) error`, `Init(ctx context.Context, args ...any) error`,\n   etc. — rejects the current zero-arg `s.Init()` callsites that exist in\n   external packages.\n\n3. The bead's PROPOSED FIX and NON-SCOPE explicitly forbid touching external\n   callers (\"Do not touch the external caller sweep in this bead\";\n   \"NON-SCOPE: Caller migration in cli/cmd, cli/internal/agent,\n   cli/internal/server, cli/internal/escalation, and metrics packages.\")\n   and AC4 requires \"no caller-package changes in this bead.\"\n\n4. AC3 requires `lefthook run pre-commit` to pass, which runs\n   `go build -buildvcs=false -v ./...` from cli/ (lefthook.yml:122-129).\n   That build covers every package in the module, including all the\n   external caller packages NON-SCOPE forbids touching.\n\n5. Concrete external breakage if AC1 is implemented today\n   (`grep -rE '\\b(store|s)\\.(Init|Create|Update|Get|Close|ReadAll|GenID|GetWithArchive|ReadAllFiltered)\\(' cli/ --include='*.go'`):\n     - 174 Go files reference these Store methods.\n     - 73 distinct files outside cli/internal/bead/ use the zero-arg\n       `store.Init()` form (e.g. cli/cmd/ac_test.go:37,\n       cli/cmd/bead_human_test.go:20, cli/internal/agent/...,\n       cli/internal/server/...).\n     - Production-code stragglers without ctx exist too:\n         cli/cmd/bead.go:414  s.GetWithArchive(args[0])\n         cli/cmd/bead.go:1281 s.Close(id)\n         cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:4485 store.Get(id)\n         cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:4811 store.Update(beadID, ...)\n   `go build ./...` and the lefthook go-build hook will fail at every one\n   of those callsites the instant Init/Get/Update/Close/ReadAll/GenID/\n   GetWithArchive/ReadAllFiltered become non-variadic ctx-first. There is\n   no signature shape that satisfies AC1 while preserving all current\n   call patterns (Go does not allow same-name method overloads on a\n   single receiver type).\n\n6. Step 0 size envelope is also exceeded for the only resolution that\n   preserves AC1+AC3: the necessary mechanical caller sweep crosses ~170\n   files in five packages (cmd, internal/agent, internal/server,\n   internal/attemptmetrics, internal/agentmetrics) — well past the\n   \"~500 lines across ~5+ files in unrelated packages\" guardrail. That\n   is exactly the sweep that NON-SCOPE excludes, and the parent split\n   (TD-027 / ddx-464feba2) was rejected for the same reason.\n\nOperator action requested:\n\n  Re-scope this bead to one of:\n\n  (a) Add the caller-package migration to scope (delete the NON-SCOPE\n      block and AC4's \"no caller-package changes\"). This becomes the\n      original TD-027 sweep that previously failed as too large; if\n      pursued, expect a multi-file diff across cli/cmd,\n      cli/internal/agent, cli/internal/server,\n      cli/internal/attemptmetrics, cli/internal/agentmetrics.\n\n  (b) Replace AC3 with a narrower verification (e.g. \"go test\n      ./internal/bead/... and go vet ./internal/bead/... pass\"), and\n      explicitly accept that `go build ./...` and lefthook pre-commit\n      will be red until follow-up caller-migration beads land. The\n      follow-up beads would then re-establish AC3 once the sweep is\n      complete.\n\n  (c) Replace AC1 with an additive shape that does not rename or\n      retype the existing variadic methods — e.g. \"add new ctx-first\n      Store methods with distinct names (InitCtx / GetCtx / …) so the\n      legacy variadic surface stays in place during the migration\",\n      then a follow-up bead deletes the variadic methods after the\n      caller sweep finishes. This satisfies the spirit of TD-027\n      (introducing the typed ctx-first surface in the bead package\n      first) without breaking the build outside the package.\n\nNo code changes were made on this attempt. Request was triaged\nstrictly against the bead body — no /tmp scratch files, no work\noutside the worktree.\nresult_rev=86de1c4af53756b734ad140cde3d260de5d1c922\nbase_rev=86de1c4af53756b734ad140cde3d260de5d1c922\noutcome_reason=no_changes","created_at":"2026-05-16T04:51:05.889445147Z","kind":"execute-bead","source":"ddx work","summary":"no_changes"},{"actor":"","body":"{\"accepted_fingerprint\":\"\",\"accepted_prompt_fingerprint\":\"\",\"from_status\":\"proposed\",\"operator_required\":true,\"prompt_fingerprint\":\"09856c6d43c0aaae4afa35dd6485b8f71942b35c4b3b0a85cf0ad892e69a26e3\",\"reason\":\"set lifecycle status\",\"source\":\"ddx bead update\",\"to_status\":\"open\"}","created_at":"2026-06-02T00:11:19.816112169Z","kind":"triaged","source":"ddx bead update","summary":"operator accepted proposed bead"},{"actor":"erik","body":"{\"decision\":\"warn\",\"decision_source\":\"pre_claim_intake\",\"detail\":\"unknown classification \\\"refinable\\\": expected one of ready, needs_refine, needs_split, operator_required, system_unready\",\"fingerprint\":\"02553f0ef79948438d572808ca581f572282a55519385a869e44cfbcb8713efe\",\"policy_mode\":\"warn-only\",\"reason\":\"system_unready\",\"rule_id\":\"pre_claim_intake.system_unready\",\"suggested_action\":\"revise the rewrite so it preserves every explicit commitment\",\"warning_fingerprint\":\"02553f0ef79948438d572808ca581f572282a55519385a869e44cfbcb8713efe\"}","created_at":"2026-06-02T00:13:17.042242734Z","kind":"intake.warn","source":"ddx work","summary":"system_unready"},{"actor":"erik","body":"{\"attempt_id\":\"20260602T001317-18b51b41\",\"bead_id\":\"ddx-3fd19af1\",\"budget\":\"30m0s\",\"diagnosis\":\"phase-empty heartbeats (harness/model/route empty) persisted past the 30m0s budget while phase=\\\"running\\\"; released lease and flagged for operator attention\",\"last_activity_at\":\"2026-06-02T00:43:17Z\",\"reason\":\"progress_watchdog\"}","created_at":"2026-06-02T