d and deterministic, with no caller-package changes in this bead.\",\"coverage\":\"Named deterministic tests are covered by Child 1 AC4, Child 2 AC5, Child 3 AC4, and Child 4 AC3. The original no-caller-package-changes clause is non_scope for Children 1-3 because parent AC1 plus parent AC3 cannot both pass after changing Store signatures unless affected external callsites are migrated; Child 4 AC4 preserves the no-caller-package-change constraint after the sweeps close.\"},{\"parent_ac\":\"NON-SCOPE: Caller migration in cli/cmd, cli/internal/agent, cli/internal/server, cli/internal/escalation, and metrics packages.\",\"coverage\":\"non_scope: preserving this item makes parent AC1 and AC3 mutually unsatisfiable. Children 1-3 relax it only for callsites of the methods each child migrates; Child 4 preserves it completely.\"},{\"parent_ac\":\"NON-SCOPE: Event method ctx threading (AppendEvent, Events, EventsByKind).\",\"coverage\":\"Preserved in every child NON-SCOPE section.\"},{\"parent_ac\":\"NON-SCOPE: Removing workflow helper methods beyond the foundational signatures this bead changes.\",\"coverage\":\"Preserved in every child NON-SCOPE section.\"},{\"parent_ac\":\"Governing artifact reference: TD-027 / spec:TD-027.\",\"coverage\":\"Preserved in every child GOVERNING ARTIFACT section and labels array.\"},{\"parent_ac\":\"Dependency/reference ID: ddx-464feba2.\",\"coverage\":\"Preserved in every child PARENT/DEPS section as the parent/split source.\"}],\"child_ids\":[\"ddx-3e8ba14b\",\"ddx-cc298105\",\"ddx-38801c65\",\"ddx-c887a63f\"],\"rationale\":\"The failed attempt showed that changing Store methods to typed ctx-first signatures while forbidding caller-package edits cannot satisfy lefthook, because Go has no overloads and existing zero-argument or legacy-argument callsites stop compiling. The split therefore groups the migration by method family: setup/id, reads, mutations, and final interface assertions. Each method-family child can update only the callsites f