.ddx/beads.jsonl:241:{"acceptance":"1. All 15 children closed.\n2. ExecuteBeadWorker.Run replaced by work.Worker.Drain (~30 lines).\n3. 18 store-error-as-loop-exit smells eliminated; transient store error during outcome-commit logs and continues.\n4. attempted/hookFailed maps deleted; pick derives exclusion from drain.result.\n5. Routing preflight runs once at Drain startup, never per iteration.\n6. ddx work mode semantics preserved: default is drain-until-no-ready-work; --once runs one ready bead then exits; --watch stays alive and sleeps for the idle interval when no execution-ready beads exist; --idle-interval without --watch is a usage error; no public compatibility alias remains for the removed polling flag.\n7. ddx try \u003cbead-id\u003e CLI command exists.\n8. File/identifier rename per package split complete; ExecuteBead* shims deleted.\n9. JSONL event shapes (bead.result, execute-bead, review, routing, triage-decision, loop-error) unchanged - verified by C0 fixture baseline.\n10. Server worker integration (cli/internal/server/) compiles and behaves identically except for the explicit once/drain/watch mode contract; tests green at every phase.\n11. ddx-c6e3db02, ddx-b24e9630, ddx-cfedee8e, ddx-a8718bec, ddx-dc157075, ddx-f9acb86d, ddx-7dcbd40b, ddx-8b7ed960, and ddx-dc300be9 behaviors preserved per C5/C9/C10 absorption ACs.\n12. FEAT-006 + FEAT-010 cross-refs updated to reflect new package paths and the mode + idle_interval worker-loop vocabulary.","created_at":"2026-05-02T19:58:24.112207288Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ddx-5cb6e6cd","depends_on_id":"ddx-12de0acc","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-02T20:00:48Z"},{"issue_id":"ddx-5cb6e6cd","depends_on_id":"ddx-7e1fed08","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-07T16:13:06Z"}],"description":"ExecuteBeadWorker.Run() is a 700-line function with 24 returns: 4 legitimate terminal exits, 1 legacy idle-loop exit, 1 routing-preflight-kills-worker exit, and 18 store-error escalations from the same handleOutcomeStoreError pattern repeated across outcome paths. The implicit state machine in the loop is real and coherent (Pick -\u003e Gate -\u003e Claim -\u003e Execute -\u003e Classify -\u003e Reviewing -\u003e Terminal) but written as conditional soup instead of explicit state.\n\n## Three-package split aligned to FEAT-010\n\n  cli/internal/agent/run/   - Layer 1: invocation atom (existing dispatch + runner)\n  cli/internal/agent/try/   - Layer 2: bead attempt (worktree, prompt, single Execute, Land, conflict-recovery, post-merge review, triage)\n  cli/internal/agent/work/  - Layer 3: queue drain (pick, claim, heartbeat, drain-loop control, stop conditions)\n\ntry.Attempt(beadID) returns sealed Outcome { Disposition (enum), Cooldown, ParkReason, RecordEvents }. Loop becomes approximately 30 lines: pick -\u003e guard -\u003e claim -\u003e attemptWithHeartbeat -\u003e applyOutcome. Single commitOutcome helper deletes the 18 store-error returns.\n\n## Ordering: refactor-LAST per user decision\n\nIn-flight Group A beads (c6e3db02 rate-limit, b24e9630 no_changes, cfedee8e ladder wire, a8718bec cost-cap reviewer) land first against current code. dc157075 tactical worker-stay-alive lands first as operational bridge. The stdout/watch-mode beads (ddx-7d9e1e82, ddx-f9acb86d, ddx-7dcbd40b, ddx-8b7ed960, ddx-dc300be9) define the public work-loop contract this refactor must preserve. THIS refactor lands last and absorbs all intervening behavior into the new architecture. Per-child ACs explicitly call out which in-flight bead's behavior each child must preserve.\n\n## Naming and public semantics\n\nPackage = try (not try_bead - Go idiom). Function = try.Attempt(beadID). Loop = work.Worker.Drain. CLI surface is ddx run / ddx try / ddx work. ddx work has three modes: once (one ready bead then exit), drain (default: run ready work until no execution-ready beads remain, then exit), and watch (stay alive indefinitely, sleep for idle interval when no execution-ready beads exist, and poll for newly arriving work). The removed polling flag is not preserved as a public compatibility alias; the durable vocabulary is mode plus idle_interval.\n\n## Children\n\n  C0  Pre-refactor JSONL fixture baseline for event-shape regression detection\n  C1  try.Outcome sealed sum type + Disposition enum + ParkReason vocabulary enumeration\n  C2  try.Attempt function shell (wraps existing executor; no behavior change)\n  C3  Move review verdict handling into try.Attempt (180 lines from loop body)\n  C4  Move conflict recovery into try.Attempt\n  C5  Move no_changes adjudication, decomposition, push-failed, push-conflict (absorbs ddx-b24e9630, ddx-c6e3db02 behavior)\n  C6  Single commitOutcome helper; deletes 18 store-error exit paths + handleOutcomeStoreError\n  C7  Uniform Guard contract; delete attempted/hookFailed maps; pick() derives from drain.result\n  C8  Routing preflight moves to Drain startup (runs once, not per iteration)\n  C9  First-class StopCondition enum + cost-cap relocation + downstream-consumer audit for execution_failed:max-cost grep before relocation. Includes queue snapshot plumbing and human-review blocker pressure from ddx-7dcbd40b.\n  C10 ddx work once/drain/watch modes + transient idle substate. Watch mode owns idle interval sleeps, per-idle queue status, and next-ready transition messaging from ddx-f9acb86d and ddx-8b7ed960.\n  C11 Heartbeat extracted to withHeartbeat helper\n  C12 Single phase-event emission (replaces 4 sites)\n  C13 File and identifier rename per package split + ADD ddx try CLI command + handle dc157075 file-path migration if it landed first\n  C14 Delete ExecuteBead* shims; verify all callers ported off (grep audit)","events":[{"actor":"ddx bead doctor","body":"dependencies→removed dangling ddx-a8718bec (1 edge(s))\ndependencies→removed dangling ddx-b24e9630 (1 edge(s))\ndependencies→removed dangling ddx-c6e3db02 (1 edge(s))\ndependencies→removed dangling ddx-dc157075 (1 edge(s))\ndependencies→removed dangling ddx-e3f25fdb (1 edge(s))\ndependencies→removed dangling ddx-fcdbc731 (1 edge(s))","created_at":"2026-06-08T04:25:18.447114877Z","kind":"repair","source":"ddx bead doctor --fix","summary":"doctor repair applied: 6 change(s)"}],"id":"ddx-5cb6e6cd","issue_type":"epic","labels":["area:agent","phase:2","refactor"],"notes":"Superseded by ddx-f088a3fd / ddx-b194d20f and audited by ddx-bdc0065e. The execute-bead -\u003e try/work package-split epic still routes through cli/internal/agent and preserves removed ddx agent compatibility assumptions, so it must not dispatch.","parent":"ddx-b18d9ce6","priority":1,"schema_version":1,"status":"cancelled","title":"REFACTOR: execute-bead surface → try / work packages aligned to FEAT-010","updated_at":"2026-06-08T04:25:18.447114877Z"}
.ddx/beads.jsonl:259:{"acceptance":"See bead body — 3 verifiable AC items: unit tests covering the four classification scenarios; lefthook green; manual smoke confirming worker emits 'server unreachable' instead of flagging beads when server is down.","closing_commit_sha":"dfcfd20746248a07bd78a93f40659012f9de3ab9","created_at":"2026-06-01T01:13:59.24088712Z","description":"**Problem**\n\nWhen `ddx work --watch` runs against a `ddx server` that is partially\nunavailable (e.g. TLS handshake failure, agent-service connection\nrefusal, persistent route-resolution failures with no candidates), the\nworker treats every individual bead as the failure unit. Each attempt\ngets flagged with `operator_attention` via the progress-watchdog or\n`execution_failed` via the routing preflight, then the next bead is\ntried, then the next.\n\nResult: a single server-side problem (one bad TLS cert, an expired\nprovider credential, a stale model catalog) silently turns the entire\nready queue into \"needs human\" beads, even though the *beads* are fine\n— the *server* is broken. The worker keeps idling, the operator sees\n\"0 closures in 24h\" with no clear signal that this is environmental.\n\nObserved concretely on niflheim on 2026-05-31:\n\n- `ddx server` was serving a TLS cert from\n  `$DDX_PROJECT_ROOT/.ddx/server/tls/cert.pem` (Apr 17 fingerprint)\n  while the client `ddx work` pinned the cert in `~/.ddx/server/tls/`\n  (May 18 fingerprint). The server logged\n  `http: TLS handshake error from 127.0.0.1:XXXXX: remote error: tls:\n  bad certificate` every ~5 min for ~36 hours.\n- Every `niflheim-71365a9f` attempt during that window failed with\n  `ResolveRoute: no viable routing candidate: 16 candidates rejected,\n  outcome_reason=no_viable_provider`.\n- After 15+ attempts the worker flagged the bead for operator\n  attention, then quietly idled with `execution-ready=0 blocked=47\n  operator-attention=17 needs-human/investigation=10`. No clear\n  signal to the operator that the *server* was the cause.\n\n**Desired behavior**\n\nThe worker should detect server-level failures separately from\nbead-level failures. Two-tier classification:\n\n1. **Bead-level failure** (current behavior): the bead's tests/lint\n   fail, the agent commits something invalid, etc. → mark the bead\n   `execution_failed`, retry per policy, eventually\n   `operator-attention`.\n2. **Server-level failure** (new): TLS handshake error, agent-service\n   connection refused, persistent `no_viable_provider` across ≥ K\n   distinct beads in the last M minutes (default K=3, M=10) → mark\n   the *server* unavailable, NOT the individual beads. Loop into a\n   probe-and-resume mode: every 30 s ping\n   `https://server/api/health`; the moment the server returns 200\n   and a small `ddx run --text` smoke test succeeds, re-enter the\n   queue. None of the beads attempted during the server-failure\n   window get penalized.\n\nThe server-failure backoff prevents the per-bead operator-attention\nflagging storm we observed. It also makes the actual root cause\nvisible — `ddx work` should emit a single distinctive log line\n(\"server unreachable: holding queue until /api/health returns\") and\nexpose that state via `ddx work status` so the operator notices it.\n\n**In-scope files (likely; verify before edit)**\n\n- `cli/internal/agent/service_run.go` — wraps `ResolveRoute` →\n  classification site for routing failures.\n- `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead*.go` — the place where\n  `no_viable_provider` is turned into `outcome_reason` for the bead.\n- The watcher loop in `cli/internal/work/` (or wherever `ddx work\n  --watch` lives) — needs the new server-unavailable state machine.\n- `cli/internal/agent/` — health-probe helper.\n- New unit tests covering: (a) K consecutive `no_viable_provider`\n  across distinct bead IDs trips server-failure mode; (b)\n  server-failure backoff doesn't penalize the beads it was about to\n  try; (c) successful health probe transitions back to normal queue\n  drain; (d) TLS handshake error from the server is classified as\n  server-level regardless of bead.\n\n**Acceptance**\n\n1. `go test ./cli/internal/agent/... ./cli/internal/work/...` passes\n   with the new tests above.\n2. `lefthook run pre-commit` (or equivalent gates) green.\n3. Manual smoke: stop `ddx server`, run `ddx work --watch`; observe\n   the worker emits \"server unreachable\" within 30 s and does NOT\n   flag any beads for operator attention while the server is down.\n   Restart `ddx server`; observe queue drain resumes.\n\n**Out of scope**\n\n- Auto-repairing server-side issues (TLS cert refresh, credential\n  rotation). Operator still has to fix the server. The worker just\n  has to detect and not amplify the failure.\n- Multi-server failover.\n- Changing the existing per-bead `operator-attention` semantics —\n  those stay for true bead-level failures.\n\n**Severity**: P1. Prevents quiet queue-stall pattern that wastes\noperator hours on triage when the actual cause is environmental.","events_attachment":"ddx-658cb394/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-658cb394","issue_type":"task","labels":["area:work","area:agent","kind:reliability","kind:operator-experience"],"priority":1,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-072824dd","status":"closed","title":"ddx work: detect server-level failures separately from bead-level (don't flag beads when server is unavailable)","updated_at":"2026-06-07T09:13:54.144477435Z"}
.ddx/beads.jsonl:266:{"acceptance":"1. `TestExecuteBeadResult_NiflheimEvidence_LandCoordinationDecisionAudit` proves result JSON/event bodies include `failure_class`, `retry_action`, `escalation_count`, requested/actual routing facts, land/reconcile status, and any review status available for the land coordination scenarios.\n2. Existing behavior from `ddx-2965925e` and `ddx-b2846610` remains covered by reuse/alignment with their helpers or by waiting on those dependencies; this bead does not add a duplicate low-level index-contention or timeout implementation.","closing_commit_sha":"4462d68f26cec2de7041cb548ff198a8261aaffa","created_at":"2026-06-08T18:36:52.228910439Z","description":"PROBLEM\nParent bead ddx-bced4e39 is too broad for one execution pass. This child owns part 2 of 3 of that parent scope.\n\nROOT CAUSE\nPROBLEM\nNiflheim land/ref/index/evidence-staging failures were recorded as overall `execution_failed` even when the candidate had succeeded or landed. The worker retried implementation work instead of reconciling land/evidence state or sending the bead to operator attention, wasting route attempts and confusing system failure with model-quality failure.\n\nROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\n- `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_orchestrator.go:305-309` wraps `LandingAdvancer` errors as generic `land advancer` errors.\n- `cli/internal/agent/failclass/failclass.go:103-142` contains the normative table that only `OutcomeGenuineFailure` can escalate, but execute-bead/work land outcomes are not consistently reduced to this typed table before retry/escalation decisions.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\nAdd self-contained Niflheim-style land coordination fixtures or table-driven cases under `cli/internal/agent/...` for `cannot lock ref refs/heads/main` after a candidate or merge is already landed, and for `landing worktree has staged changes after waiting 2s` caused by generated DDx evidence. Classify these as land/ref/index/evidence coordination outcomes, not implementation/model failures. If the candidate commit or merge is already an ancestor of the target, reconcile and close/continue without rerunning implementation. If the landing worktree is dirty with generated evidence or DDx metadata, retry/preserve the land/evidence step or move to operator attention according to existing reliability policy.\n\nNON-SCOPE\n- Do not change Fizeau route selection or hard-code concrete provider/model names.\n- Do not edit Niflheim beads or Niflheim implementation code.\n- Do not duplicate the low-level index-contention fix tracked by `ddx-2965925e`; reuse or align with it.\n- Do not duplicate the post-commit review/land timeout work tracked by `ddx-b2846610`; this is typed classification and reconciliation behavior, not another timeout implementation.\n- Do not duplicate the repeated pre-claim warn operator-attention bead `ddx-d67f124e`.\n- Do not implement a full operator-lane product workflow beyond state transitions/events needed to keep the worker from blind retry or false close.\n\nINTERSECTIONS\nParent: `ddx-3106674f`. Dependencies to preserve: `ddx-2965925e`, `ddx-b2846610`, `ddx-d67f124e`. Related: `ddx-e1a576a7`, `ddx-a9d130d0`, `ddx-ac10e7af`. Governing references: FEAT-010, TP-021, ADR-024, docs/dev/engineer\n...[truncated]\n\nPROPOSED FIX\nImplement only this child acceptance slice:\n- `TestExecuteBeadResult_NiflheimEvidence_LandCoordinationDecisionAudit` proves result JSON/event bodies include `failure_class`, `retry_action`, `escalation_count`, requested/actual routing facts, land/reconcile status, and any review status available for the land coordination scenarios.\n- Existing behavior from `ddx-2965925e` and `ddx-b2846610` remains covered by reuse/alignment with their helpers or by waiting on those dependencies; this bead does not add a duplicate low-level index-contention or timeout implementation.\n\nNON-SCOPE\nDo not implement parent acceptance criteria assigned to sibling child beads. Preserve every parent non-scope constraint unless this child explicitly narrows it.","events_attachment":"ddx-67cdc109/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-67cdc109","issue_type":"task","labels":["phase:iterate","area:agent","area:execute-bead","area:workers","area:review","kind:bug","kind:reliability","severity:critical","spec:FEAT-010","spec:TP-021","adr:024","incident:niflheim-2026-06-06","prevention","decomposed"],"parent":"ddx-bced4e39","priority":0,"queue-rank":2160,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-fe96ce02","status":"closed","title":"Classify land coordination failures without implementation reruns: part 2","updated_at":"2026-06-28T02:15:39.446124448Z"}
.ddx/beads.jsonl:271:{"acceptance":"1. cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go between the existing NoReadyWork branch and the sleepOrWake call hosts the diagnose→remediate→rescan logic described above.\n2. cli/cmd/work.go exposes --no-auto-supersede-close, --no-auto-epic-decompose, --no-auto-closure-reclassify flags; cli/internal/config defaults work.autoRemediations.{autoSupersedeClose,autoEpicDecompose,autoClosureReclassify} to true.\n3. TestWorkIdle_AutoRemediatesAndRescansWithoutSleep: fixture with one mislabeled closure-candidate epic + one supersession leftover; ddx work --once auto-resolves both in a single loop iteration, emits loop.auto_remediated event with counts, no sleep, returns drained.\n4. TestWorkIdle_AutoDecomposeUndecomposedEpic: fixture with one genuinely-undecomposed epic that satisfies all RC-6 preconditions; loop dispatches exactly one AutoDecomposeEpic call, child beads are filed, parent epic execution_eligible=false, loop re-scans and picks one child.\n5. TestWorkIdle_AutoDecomposeRespectsCostBudget: --max-recovery-cost=0; loop diagnoses genuinely_needs_decomposition but does NOT dispatch; bead is surfaced as gated_by_budget_or_cooldown.\n6. TestWorkIdle_AtMostOneDecomposePerIteration: fixture with three genuinely-undecomposed epics; one loop iteration dispatches exactly one decompose; subsequent iterations handle the remaining two.\n7. TestWorkIdle_OverrideFlagSuppressesDecompose: --no-auto-epic-decompose set; loop does NOT dispatch even when all preconditions pass; bead is surfaced as gated_by_budget_or_cooldown with detail \"no-auto-epic-decompose\".\n8. TestWorkIdle_NoSuccessFallsThroughToSleep: only beads with non-remediable diagnoses present; loop falls through to existing sleepOrWake path, emits loop.idle, behavior matches today.\n9. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... ./cmd/... -count=1 green.\n10. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./... green.\n11. lefthook run pre-commit passes.","created_at":"2026-05-16T16:58:41.80484238Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ddx-68b48c9e","depends_on_id":"ddx-79e66725","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-16T16:58:46Z"},{"issue_id":"ddx-68b48c9e","depends_on_id":"ddx-04e89823","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-16T16:58:46Z"},{"issue_id":"ddx-68b48c9e","depends_on_id":"ddx-7b88e3a7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-16T16:58:47Z"}],"description":"PROBLEM\ncli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:1263-1315 today reads ReadyExecutionBreakdown into result.NoReadyWorkDetail, emits loop.idle, and either returns (--once / drain) or sleeps (--watch). It never diagnoses or auto-remediates. FEAT-010 §Idle-Path Diagnosis and Auto-Remediation requires the loop to diagnose every non-ready bead, fire matching remediators, and re-scan without sleeping when at least one remediation succeeded.\n\nROOT CAUSE\nNo diagnose+dispatch logic exists at the insertion point.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\nInside execute_bead_loop.go, after ReadyExecutionBreakdown populates breakdown (~line 1265) and before applyStop/sleepOrWake (~line 1271), insert the idle-path auto-remediation block.\n\nPseudo-flow (translate to Go):\n1. Build childIndex, openChildIndex, depIndex from the store (these may already be computed inside ReadyExecutionBreakdown; expose them or rebuild as needed).\n2. Walk breakdown.Epics ∪ breakdown.DepWaiting ∪ breakdown.OperatorAttention. For each bead, call bead.Diagnose(...) (from cli/internal/bead/diagnose.go).\n3. Switch on the BlockReasonCode:\n   - superseded_pending_close: queue a no-op (the cascade happens automatically inside any subsequent Close(); to actively trigger it on a known X, call store.Close on the SUPERSEDER Y if it's somehow still open in this branch — typically not; if X is the bead and Y is already closed but the cascade never ran, call a new store.RunSupersededCascade(X, Y) helper that runs the same scope-checked cascade out of band).\n   - closure_candidate_misclassified: this should disappear once the RC-1 classifier fix lands; if it still appears, log and surface (defensive).\n   - dead_intermediate_all_children_closed: trigger the existing closure-evaluation path against the bead.\n   - dead_intermediate_open_children_pending OR epic_of_epic: skip (recursion via children handles it).\n   - genuinely_needs_decomposition: queue an AutoDecomposeEpic call. At most ONE auto-decompose dispatch per loop iteration (track a counter). Skip if --no-auto-epic-decompose set.\n   - dep_blocked_by, parent_child_state_conflict, claimed_in_progress, provider_route_unavailable, gated_by_budget_or_cooldown, malformed_parent_or_dep_ref, dependency_cycle, closed_or_missing_parent, auto_remediation_exhausted, no_diagnosis: no idle-path action; will surface via ddx work focus.\n   - stale_graph_index: trigger an index rebuild and re-diagnose next loop.\n4. Execute queued remediations sequentially. Track count of successes.\n5. If any remediation succeeded, emit loop.auto_remediated event with {remediation_counts: {...}, total_attempted, total_succeeded}, clearTransientCandidateSkips, and `continue` (re-scan without entering sleepOrWake).\n6. If none succeeded, fall through to the existing emit(\"loop.idle\", ...) + sleepOrWake path.\n\nAdd operator override flags to cli/cmd/work.go: --no-auto-supersede-close, --no-auto-epic-decompose, --no-auto-closure-reclassify. Plumb them through to the work loop via runtime config (mirror how existing --max-recovery-cost flows in).\n\nAdd config key work.autoRemediations: { autoSupersedeClose: bool, autoEpicDecompose: bool, autoClosureReclassify: bool } with defaults of true. Flags override config; per-project config overrides defaults.\n\nReuse existing cost budget threading: AutoDecomposeEpic counts against --max-recovery-cost just like the existing post-TooLarge decomposer does. Honor SmartRetryCooldown / SetExecutionCooldown precedent for per-bead cooldown after failed auto-decompose (already implemented in the auto_decompose_epic bead).\n\nNON-SCOPE\n- Implementing the diagnoser, RC-1 fix, RC-2 cascade, RC-3 walk-up, RC-6 handler — those are separate beads this one depends on.\n- Operator surface changes (ddx work focus, ddx work plan) — separate beads.\n\nPARENT AND DEPS\nParent: ddx-2a1ece2b. Depends on ddx-79e66725 (diagnose), ddx-e9f3adaf (RC-1 lifecycle), ddx-04e89823 (RC-2 cascade), ddx-f500c75b (RC-3 walk-up), ddx-7b88e3a7 (RC-6 auto-decompose handler).","events":[{"actor":"erik","body":"{\"decision\":\"warn\",\"decision_source\":\"pre_claim_intake\",\"detail\":\"blocking dependencies prevent execution: Bead is well-authored with clear design specification (pseudo-code), precise execution points (file:line), comprehensive AC with named tests, and clean scope boundaries. However, execution is blocked by 5 explicit dependency beads (ddx-79e66725, ddx-e9f3adaf, ddx-04e89823, ddx-f500c75b, ddx-7b88e3a7) that must be completed and merged before implementation can begin. Once dependencies resolve, this bead is immediately executable.\",\"fingerprint\":\"a19538906cb683c0d861aac7c374051ceffe2a63340350c6e80561f768651a14\",\"policy_mode\":\"warn-only\",\"reason\":\"readiness_best_effort\",\"rule_id\":\"pre_claim_intake.readiness_best_effort\",\"suggested_action\":\"revise the rewrite so it preserves every explicit commitment\",\"warning_fingerprint\":\"a19538906cb683c0d861aac7c374051ceffe2a63340350c6e80561f768651a14\"}","created_at":"2026-05-28T14:50:29.389828023Z","kind":"intake.warn","source":"ddx work","summary":"readiness_best_effort"},{"actor":"erik","body":"{\"decision\":\"warn\",\"decision_source\":\"pre_claim_intake\",\"detail\":\"readiness route unavailable: lifecycle dispatch: project root mutation rejected (changed existing dirty paths: .ddx/beads.jsonl)\",\"fingerprint\":\"e050f98fd02ceb82376ad67098871ad3c20e9b729038d4a1358c77a0d9132996\",\"policy_mode\":\"warn-only\",\"reason\":\"system_unready\",\"rule_id\":\"pre_claim_intake.system_unready\",\"suggested_action\":\"revise the rewrite so it preserves every explicit commitment\",\"warning_