.ddx/beads.jsonl:277:{"acceptance":"1. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... ./cmd/... -run 'NiflheimEvidence|PreClaim|RetryEscalation|PreClaimDecisionAudit' -count=1` passes.\n2. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... ./cmd/... -count=1` passes.\n3. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.","created_at":"2026-06-08T16:59:04.8421817Z","description":"PROBLEM\nParent bead ddx-eea2dfca is too broad for one execution pass. This child owns part 3 of 3 of that parent scope.\n\nROOT CAUSE\nPROBLEM\nA Niflheim worker repeatedly emitted pre-claim readiness/intake warnings for the same systemic dirty/generated DDx artifact condition and continued polling/releasing. That looks like forward progress but does not create a clear operator-visible system-unready lane after the configured threshold.\n\nROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\n- `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:1967-2072` emits pre-claim timeout/system-unready outcomes as warn-only by default and continues implementation when strict intake blocking is off.\n- `cli/internal/agent/failclass/failclass.go:103-142` says setup/dirty worktree/system outcomes should not escalate, but repeated pre-claim warnings are not consistently classified into retry/operator-attention decisions before worker retry loops continue.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\nAdd a self-contained Niflheim-style pre-claim fixture or table-driven case under `cli/internal/agent/...` for repeated readiness timeout/system-unready warnings with generated DDx artifact dirt such as `.ddx/harness-sessions/...json`. After the configured same-fingerprint threshold, classify the condition as system-unready/operator-attention and release/park without implementation retry or model escalation. Align with `ddx-d67f124e` rather than duplicating its lower-level implementation.\n\nNON-SCOPE\n- Do not change Fizeau route selection or hard-code concrete provider/model names.\n- Do not edit Niflheim beads or Niflheim implementation code.\n- Do not duplicate the low-level index-c