.ddx/beads.jsonl:278:{"created_at":"2026-05-21T03:25:29.25797088Z","description":"PROBLEM\nThe docker-clone attempt backend is unusable on a remote, rootless, or de-nested Docker daemon (e.g. OrbStack on this machine, docker info Name=orbstack). Every attempt fast-fails in 17-39ms before any agent work with: docker: Error response from daemon: invalid mount config for type \"bind\": bind source path does not exist: \u003chost path\u003e. Outcome is classified execution_failed / transport.\n\nROOT CAUSE\ncli/internal/agent/attempt_backend.go:612 dockerRunArgs() constructs the container with five classes of HOST bind-mount (--mount type=bind,src=\u003chostpath\u003e):\n  - :622 src=ws.WorkDir            dst=/work               (cloned repo)\n  - :623 src=exe                   dst=/usr/local/bin/ddx  (ddx binary, os.Executable())\n  - :636 src=ws.DockerRun          dst=/ddx-runtime        (HOME/cache/tmp + injected creds)\n  - :641-642 gocache, work-tmp                              (Go build/test cache)\n  - :644-649 dockerToolMounts() -\u003e claude/codex/gemini      (agent CLIs via exec.LookPath)\nA de-nested/remote daemon's filesystem namespace does not include this machine's /home/erik/... , so every src path 'does not exist' from the daemon's view. Confirmed: 4 attempts on ddx-b5816493 failed this way; failing paths included /home/erik/.local/bin/ddx and /home/erik/.local/share/claude/versions/2.1.145. A short -v probe 'succeeded' only because docker silently auto-created an empty dir (the classic -v footgun), proving the source was not visible.\n\nPROPOSED FIX (decomposed into child tasks)\nAdopt the standard create -\u003e cp -\u003e start -\u003e cp-out -\u003e rm pattern used for remote/rootless daemons, plus bake static tooling into the image and use daemon-managed named volumes for caches. Only the daemon's own storage (image layers + named volumes) is reliably reachable; everything dynamic is copied in/out.\n  1. Bake agent CLIs into the attempt-runner image; drop their bind-mounts.\n  2. Keystone: move workspace + ddx binary in via docker create/cp instead of bind.\n  3. Convert Go caches + runtime dir to named volumes.\n  4. Inject credentials via env/docker cp instead of the runtime-home bind.\n\nNON-SCOPE\n- The worktree and local-clone backends (unaffected; worktree is the working default).\n- Routing/provider selection.\n\nNOTE: filed from an operator session after switching the live queue drain to --attempt-backend worktree to work around this. Child tasks carry their own file:line scope and AC.","id":"ddx-6967f6e6","issue_type":"epic","labels":["area:agent","kind:bug","reliability","spec:FEAT-010"],"priority":2,"schema_version":1,"spec-id":"FEAT-010","status":"closed","title":"docker-clone attempt backend: eliminate host bind-mounts for remote/de-nested daemon compatibility","updated_at":"2026-06-07T18:15:42.897652643Z"}
.ddx/beads.jsonl:297:{"acceptance":"1. docs/helix/02-design/contracts/API-001-execute-bead-supervisor-contract.md contains a status table or canonical delegation that covers every `ExecuteBeadStatus*` constant in cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_status.go.\n2. Any API-001 text that still lists only five statuses is removed or explicitly scoped as a historical minimal v1 subset.\n3. `rg -n \"status.*one of|structural_validation_failed.*execution_failed.*post_run_check_failed\" docs/helix/02-design/contracts/API-001-execute-bead-supervisor-contract.md` has no stale five-status-only contract hit.\n4. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... -run TestExecuteBeadStatus` passes.\n5. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.","closing_commit_sha":"05d462e8b7f9ca2003e8f96d46a9a1e56830bf57","created_at":"2026-06-05T23:56:41.999712359Z","description":"PROBLEM\nAPI-001 documents only five supervisor-visible execute-bead statuses, but the implementation exposes a larger stable status contract used by `ddx try`, `ddx work`, retry logic, review outcomes, land conflict handling, and resource exhaustion. A worker or server consumer that follows API-001 literally will miss valid statuses.\n\nROOT CAUSE\n- docs/helix/02-design/contracts/API-001-execute-bead-supervisor-contract.md:177 lists only `structural_validation_failed`, `execution_failed`, `post_run_check_failed`, `land_conflict`, and `success`.\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_status.go:330 defines additional stable statuses including `ratchet_failed`, `push_failed`, `push_conflict`, `preserved_needs_review`, `no_evidence_produced`, `no_changes`, `already_satisfied`, `resource_exhausted`, review statuses, conflict-resolution statuses, and repair-cycle statuses.\n- docs/helix/01-frame/features/FEAT-010-task-execution.md already describes richer candidate-cycle and drain lifecycle semantics, so API-001 is stale rather than the implementation being obviously wrong.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\nUpdate API-001 to define the full supervisor-visible status taxonomy or explicitly delegate the canonical list to FEAT-010 plus the implementation enum. Add a compact status table with close/unclaim/operator-attention behavior categories and note which statuses are legacy/future-only if any are not emitted today.\n\nNON-SCOPE\nDo not change status strings or worker behavior. Do not redo landing semantics; ddx-693d504f covers that separately.","events_attachment":"ddx-72ee9fbc/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-72ee9fbc","issue_type":"task","labels":["phase:iterate","area:docs","area:agent","kind:spec","spec-drift"],"parent":"ddx-4ac4da95","priority":1,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-df425ccf","spec-id":"API-001","status":"closed","title":"docs: align API-001 execute-bead status contract","updated_at":"2026-06-07T13:47:20.328145144Z","work-no-changes-count":2}
.ddx/beads.jsonl:347:{"acceptance":"1. RoutePreflight invocation removed from per-iteration loop body in cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go (pre-refactor lines 483-510).\n2. Called once in work.Worker.Drain bootstrap before for-loop starts.\n3. Startup failure surfaces as Disposition=LoopError + ParkReason=preflight_failed message (not iteration-level execution_failed).\n4. TestDrain_RoutingPreflightRunsOnce verifies preflight called exactly once even if Drain iterates multiple beads.\n5. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... green.\n6. lefthook run pre-commit passes.","closing_commit_sha":"95bf6cf47334c2c2a787ea76d6389db6161ad028","created_at":"2026-05-02T20:02:28.250213823Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ddx-848069a3","depends_on_id":"ddx-06eb05d8","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-02T20:02:28Z"}],"description":"execute_bead_loop.go:483-510 routing preflight runs per-iteration today AND treats its rejection as a worker-terminal exit (the user's original bug #2). Move to Drain startup: run once before the for-loop. If it fails, return one worker-level execution_failed record and exit (legitimate startup failure). Never run again per iteration.\n\nINTERSECTIONS\n- P1: routing preflight should fail open when its own check rejects.\n- P2: preflight only owns startup advisory checks, not eligibility or provider availability.\n- P3: skipped preflight should surface as an explicit event.\n- P4: a preflight failure on one bead must not affect later beads.","events_attachment":"ddx-848069a3/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-848069a3","issue_type":"task","labels":["kind:fix","phase:2","reconciled:no-changes-state","refactor"],"parent":"ddx-5cb6e6cd","priority":1,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-465987e8","status":"closed","title":"C8: routing preflight moves to Drain startup (runs once, not per iteration)","updated_at":"2026-05-07T05:58:25.724907692Z"}
.ddx/beads.jsonl:356:{"acceptance":"1. TestWorkStartup_ReapsStaleWorkerDirs asserts that .ddx/workers/agent-loop-*/ directories whose status.json shows pid=dead or last_activity_at \u003e 30 min stale are removed at startup.\n2. TestExecutionsRetention_ArchivesOldEvidence asserts that .ddx/executions/\u003ctimestamp\u003e/ entries older than DDX_EXECUTION_RETAIN_DAYS are moved under .ddx/executions-archive/\u003cyear\u003e/\u003cmonth\u003e/ (or deleted if DDX_EXECUTION_RETAIN_DAYS=0).\n3. `ddx doctor` reports the count of stale worktrees, worker dirs, and execution dirs without making changes. `ddx doctor --apply` runs the reaper paths.\n4. lefthook run pre-commit passes.","claimed-at":"2026-05-15T06:35:45Z","claimed-machine":"eitri","claimed-pid":"4026275","closing_commit_sha":"bc8361424ddb5806551f6c7571add0f0c40fdd20","created_at":"2026-05-15T02:42:34.118198622Z","description":"PROBLEM\nParent bead ddx-c191e91a is too broad for one execution pass. This child owns part 2 of 3 of that parent scope.\n\nROOT CAUSE\nPROBLEM\nDDx-managed filesystem state accumulates indefinitely. On the Fizeau project (sibling repo, /Users/erik/Projects/fizeau) on 2026-05-14:\n- /var/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/ contained 9,735 inodes across ~9700+ directories. Many were .execute-bead-wt-* worktrees dating back to 2026-05-07 (a week stale). Each is a full repo checkout, multiplying repo size on disk.\n- .ddx/workers/ held 35 agent-loop-\u003cnano-id\u003e/ directories. Most show last_activity_at older than 1 hour with no live process. They keep persisting per-attempt status.json entries.\n- .ddx/executions/ held 44 attempt directories. Some have unmerged result.json state (a previous merge or worker crash left them in DU). No automatic GC.\n- .ddx/attachments/ holds 355 per-bead artifact directories. They flood `git status` as untracked since nothing gitignores them.\n\nROOT CAUSE\n- `ddx try` creates a worktree under `/var/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-\u003cbead\u003e-\u003ctimestamp\u003e-\u003chash\u003e/` and only sometimes cleans up. Failure paths (worktree_lost, execution_failed, process crash) consistently leave the worktree behind. There's no startup reaper for stale worktrees.\n- `ddx work` and `ddx try` write a worker status.json under .ddx/workers/agent-loop-\u003cnano-id\u003e/ and the writer is responsible for cleanup. Process crashes leave the directory behind; no startup reaper claims them.\n- .ddx/executions/\u003ctimestamp\u003e/ is meant to be retained as evidence (per CONTRACT-003 / FEAT-010 evidence pile). But there's no retention policy: directories accumulate forever. Some land in unmerged git state after partial commits.\n- .ddx/attachments/ and .ddx/run-state*.json are written by every ddx invocation, but the project's .gitignore policy for them is inconsistent (.ddx/executions is ignored; .ddx/attachments and .ddx/run-state.json appear in `git status` constantly).\n\nPROPOSED FIX\n1. Add a startup reaper to `ddx work` and `ddx try`: on launch, scan /var/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/, identify worktrees whose parent ddx-try/ddx-work process is dead (no PID match), `git worktree remove` + `rm -rf` them. Bound the scan to N=200 per launch so a cold start doesn't take forever. Configurable via DDX_WORKTREE_REAP_MAX_AGE (default 72h).\n2. Add a startup reaper for `.ddx/workers/agent-loop-*/`: read status.json's `pid` and `last_activity_at`; if pid is gone OR activity \u003e 30 min stale, remove the directory.\n3. Add a configurable execution-evidence retention policy:\n...[truncated]\n\nPROPOSED FIX\nImplement only this child acceptance slice:\n- TestWorkStartup_ReapsStaleWorkerDirs asserts that .ddx/workers/agent-loop-*/ directories whose status.json shows pid=dead or last_activity_at \u003e 30 min stale are removed at startup.\n- TestExecutionsRetention_ArchivesOldEvidence asserts that .ddx/executions/\u003ctimestamp\u003e/ entries older than DDX_EXECUTION_RETAIN_DAYS are moved under .ddx/executions-archive/\u003cyear\u003e/\u003cmonth\u003e/ (or deleted if DDX_EXECUTION_RETAIN_DAYS=0).\n- `ddx doctor` reports the count of stale worktrees, worker dirs, and execution dirs without making changes. `ddx doctor --apply` runs the reaper paths.\n\nNON-SCOPE\nDo not implement parent acceptance criteria assigned to sibling child beads. Preserve every parent non-scope constraint unless this child explicitly narrows it.","events_attachment":"ddx-887e2bd3/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-887e2bd3","issue_type":"task","labels":["area:agent","area:execution","kind:cleanup","decomposed"],"owner":"erik","parent":"ddx-c191e91a","priority":0,"queue-rank":450,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-6fcce6f3","status":"closed","title":"housekeeping: reap orphan ddx worktrees and stale worker/execution state: part 2","updated_at":"2026-06-13T13:58:29.130519436Z","work-heartbeat-at":"2026-05-15T06:35:45.061749456Z"}
