.ddx/beads.jsonl:384:{"acceptance":"1. cli/internal/agent/work/stop.go defines StopCondition enum: Drained | Once | Signal | Budget | NoProgress | Blocked, and drain.stop(state) is the only production budget/terminal stop classifier.\n2. Cost-cap checks are removed from executor closure call sites and reviewer group cost is charged to the same budget accumulator before close eligibility is evaluated.\n3. No-progress retry budget is incremented only for valid implementation attempts; TestStopCondition_NoProgress_IgnoresIntakeRoutingReviewAndOperatorStates covers intake block, decomposition, claim race, routing preflight, quota/transport/auth/tool setup, review-error, and needs_human cases.\n4. Review REQUEST_CHANGES/BLOCK no longer reopens a closed bead. A review_fixable_gap prevents close, records review-fixable-gap, and schedules one bounded repair cycle with repair_context_from_review_group. TestPreCloseReviewFixableGap_PreventsCloseAndSchedulesRepair covers this.\n5. review_spec_gap, review_missing_acceptance, review_too_large at depth cap, review_unsafe_or_out_of_scope, and exhausted review_error transition to blocked with needs_human and do not consume no-progress budget. TestReviewTerminalClassifications_BlockWithoutNoProgress covers this.\n6. MinPower retry/escalation behavior from ddx-cfedee8e is wired in the attempt/retry path without mutating explicit harness/model/profile pins. TestRetryPolicy_ReviewFixableGapRaisesMinPowerAndPreservesPins covers the path.\n7. Execution records include append-only cycle trace data for initial and repair cycles: cycle_index, attempt_id, result_rev, implementer route facts, review_group_id, reviewer_index values, review verdicts, and final decision. TestExecutionTrace_RecordsInitialAndRepairCycles covers both cycles.\n8. Downstream-consumer audit for cost-cap and stop-condition event names is committed to .ddx/executions/\u003crun-id\u003e/cost-cap-consumers.md.\n9. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... green.\n10. lefthook run pre-commit passes.","created_at":"2026-05-02T20:02:28.321106862Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ddx-9228a484","depends_on_id":"ddx-848069a3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-02T20:02:28Z"},{"issue_id":"ddx-9228a484","depends_on_id":"ddx-09d2990c","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-02T20:15:17Z"},{"issue_id":"ddx-9228a484","depends_on_id":"ddx-99a3be32","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-06T15:17:58Z"},{"issue_id":"ddx-9228a484","depends_on_id":"ddx-7e1fed08","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-07T16:13:58Z"}],"description":"PROBLEM\nThe execution loop now needs a single durable stop/retry policy for the reliable factory workflow. Current code still exposes older post-merge review/reopen semantics and scattered stop logic: ExecuteBeadReport.ReviewVerdict is documented as post-merge in cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:226, Reopen is documented for REQUEST_CHANGES/BLOCK at cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:300, no-progress suppression only excludes a narrow transient set at cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:1576, and C9 previously depended on ddx-cfedee8e even though C9 absorbs that scope.\n\nROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\n- cli/cmd/agent_cmd.go:1722 and cli/cmd/agent_cmd.go:1818 contain historical cost-cap stop sites outside a first-class StopCondition gate.\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:226 and cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:300 still describe post-merge reviewer close/reopen behavior, which conflicts with ADR-024 default adversarial pre-close review.\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:1576 counts no-progress by base/result equality but only excludes transport/quota/routing/timeout/merge_conflict outcome reasons; intake blocks, decomposition, review errors, and operator-required states must not consume no-progress retry budget.\n- ddx-9228a484 previously listed ddx-cfedee8e as a dependency while also absorbing it, creating a queue deadlock.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\n- Implement cli/internal/agent/work/stop.go with StopCondition values Drained, Once, Signal, Budget, NoProgress, Blocked.\n- Move all budget/cost-cap decisions, including implementer plus adversarial reviewer group cost, into drain.stop(state).\n- Relocate MinPower retry behavior from ddx-cfedee8e into the attempt/retry path without mutating requested harness/model/profile pins. A review_fixable_gap may raise MinPower for the repair attempt; spec gaps, missing acceptance, too-large, unsafe/out-of-scope, review errors beyond cap, intake ambiguity, and decomposition overflow block for the operator instead.\n- Make no-progress budget count only valid implementation attempts where checkout/context existed and the implementer had an opportunity to modify or verify code. Exclude intake rewrites/blocks/decomposition, claim races, routing preflight, quota/transport/auth/tool setup, review errors, and operator-action states.\n- Keep append-only cycle trace fields for every implementation cycle and repair cycle: cycle_index, attempt_id, result_rev, implementer route facts, review_group_id, reviewer slots, review result, final decision.\n\nNON-SCOPE\n- Implementing the adversarial review gate itself; that is tracked separately.\n- Frontend display of stop reasons.\n- Poll-interval defaults and idle workers; already handled by ddx-dc157075 / C10.","events":[{"actor":"ddx","body":"{\"resolved_provider\":\"codex\",\"resolved_model\":\"gpt-5.4-mini\",\"fallback_chain\":[],\"actual_power\":8}","created_at":"2026-05-06T09:57:33.739548542Z","kind":"routing","source":"ddx agent execute-bead","summary":"provider=codex model=gpt-5.4-mini"},{"actor":"ddx","body":"{\"attempt_id\":\"20260506T095557-abbe996b\",\"harness\":\"codex\",\"model\":\"gpt-5.4-mini\",\"input_tokens\":1639001,\"output_tokens\":9876,\"total_tokens\":1648877,\"cost_usd\":0,\"duration_ms\":93966,\"exit_code\":0}","created_at":"2026-05-06T09:57:33.982549382Z","kind":"cost","source":"ddx agent execute-bead","summary":"tokens=1648877 model=gpt-5.4-mini"},{"act