.ddx/beads.jsonl:387:{"acceptance":"1. `ddx install \u003cname\u003e --global --silent` installs the plugin to ${XDG_DATA_HOME}/ddx/global/plugins/\u003cname\u003e/ and creates a symlink or copy under ~/.claude/skills/\u003cname\u003e and ~/.agents/skills/\u003cname\u003e.\n2. `ddx install \u003cname\u003e` (no --global, in-tree mode) installs to \u003cproject\u003e/.ddx/plugins/\u003cname\u003e/ and creates project-tier links under \u003cproject\u003e/.claude/skills/\u003cname\u003e and \u003cproject\u003e/.agents/skills/\u003cname\u003e.\n3. `ddx install \u003cname\u003e` (no --global, convention mode) installs to ${XDG_DATA_HOME}/ddx/projects/\u003chost\u003e/\u003cowner\u003e/\u003crepo\u003e/plugins/\u003cname\u003e/ and creates project-tier links pointing into that XDG plugins/ path.\n4. TestPluginLookup_PrefersProjectOverGlobal asserts that when both paths have the plugin, the project copy wins.\n5. TestPluginLookup_FallsBackToGlobal asserts that when the project copy is missing, the global copy is used.\n6. TestInitGlobal_CreatesAgentTierLinks asserts ~/.claude/skills/ddx and ~/.agents/skills/ddx point into ${XDG_DATA_HOME}/ddx/global/plugins/ddx/.\n7. TestInitProject_DoesNotInstallPlugins asserts `ddx init` (in-project) does not write to plugins/ — plugins lazy-resolve from global.\n8. TestUpdateGlobal_UpdatesGlobalNotProject asserts `ddx update --global` updates only the global plugin tree.\n9. TestUpdate_RespectsConventionVsInTreeMode asserts `ddx update` (no flag) updates the project install in whichever mode is active.\n10. ddx doctor's two new lines (\"Global Install\" and \"Project Install\") render correctly.\n11. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./cmd/... ./internal/registry/... green.\n12. lefthook run pre-commit passes.\n13. Spec updates (ADR/skill-topology + CLAUDE.md Persona System) landed in this bead's commit.","created_at":"2026-05-15T01:17:34.344812284Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ddx-937de9fc","depends_on_id":"ddx-06cbaa90","type":"blocks","cr