:"ddx-937de9fc","depends_on_id":"ddx-3478153c","type":"depends_on","created_at":"2026-06-03T17:21:03Z"},{"issue_id":"ddx-937de9fc","depends_on_id":"ddx-348cf865","type":"depends_on","created_at":"2026-06-03T17:21:03Z"},{"issue_id":"ddx-937de9fc","depends_on_id":"ddx-9b105bf6","type":"depends_on","created_at":"2026-06-03T21:49:46Z"},{"issue_id":"ddx-937de9fc","depends_on_id":"ddx-864bec6b","type":"depends_on","created_at":"2026-06-03T21:49:46Z"},{"issue_id":"ddx-937de9fc","depends_on_id":"ddx-6a23cbd3","type":"depends_on","created_at":"2026-06-03T21:49:46Z"},{"issue_id":"ddx-937de9fc","depends_on_id":"ddx-7e585c0a","type":"depends_on","created_at":"2026-06-03T23:07:18Z"}],"description":"PROBLEM (Principle 2 of epic ddx-602ae31a)\n\nSkills, personas, and plugin content need to install in two distinct locations depending on operator intent:\n\n- **install-to-agent (global)**: written under the user's agent-tier paths (e.g. ~/.claude/skills/\u003cname\u003e, ~/.codex/skills/\u003cname\u003e, or the equivalent each harness reads). Skills and personas are then available across every project on the machine without per-project setup. Lives under ${XDG_DATA_HOME}/ddx/global/plugins/\u003cname\u003e/ with symlinks/copies into the agent-tier paths.\n- **install-in-project**: written under ddxroot.Path()/plugins/\u003cname\u003e/. In in-tree mode that is \u003cproject\u003e/.ddx/plugins/\u003cname\u003e/; in convention mode that is ${XDG_DATA_HOME}/ddx/projects/\u003chost\u003e/\u003cowner\u003e/\u003crepo\u003e/plugins/\u003cname\u003e/. Either way the project-scoped agent paths point into it (e.g. \u003cproject\u003e/.claude/skills/ link target).\n\nToday `ddx install`, `ddx update`, `ddx plugin list`, and `ddx init` all assume per-project installs only. There is no `--global` surface. Operators who want a single Claude Code install per machine (the common case) must repeat the install for every project.\n\nROOT CAUSE\n- cli/cmd/install.go and cli/cmd/update.go target ddxroot.Path() unconditionally.\n- cli/cmd/init.go bundles plugin install with manifest creation.\n- The agent-tier paths (~/.claude/skills/...) are written only when the operator manually links them, or via the legacy install paths that were retired (per the user's `feedback_no_local_replace` and the home-directory-install retirement noted in CLAUDE.md).\n\nPROPOSED FIX\n\n1. Add `--global` flag to `ddx install`, `ddx update`, `ddx plugin list`, `ddx plugin show`. When set:\n   - Resolve target: ${XDG_DATA_HOME}/ddx/global/plugins/\u003cname\u003e/.\n   - Write the plugin content there.\n   - Create symlinks (or copies, OS-dependent) into the agent-tier skill paths the user's agents read: ~/.claude/skills/\u003cname\u003e, ~/.codex/skills/\u003cname\u003e, and any others the agent registry knows about.\n   - Skill discovery from a fresh shell finds the skill via the agent-tier path.\n\n2. Without `--global`, `ddx install` writes to ddxroot.Path()/plugins/\u003cname\u003e/ and links into \u003cproject\u003e/.claude/skills/\u003cname\u003e AND \u003cproject\u003e/.agents/skills/\u003cname\u003e. In convention mode (no \u003cproject\u003e/.ddx/) the project's agent-tier paths still point into the XDG project dir's plugins. In in-tree mode they point into \u003cproject\u003e/.ddx/plugins/.\n\n3. `ddx init --global` is the umbrella command for first-time setup: installs the default ddx plugin globally, creates agent-tier links, and writes ${XDG_DATA_HOME}/ddx/global/config.yaml with convention defaults.\n\n4. `ddx init` (no flag) creates \u003cproject\u003e/.ddx/ and does NOT install plugins — plugins are lazy-resolved on first use, preferring the project install over global.\n\n5. Plugin lookup precedence at runtime:\n   - \u003cproject\u003e/.ddx/plugins/\u003cname\u003e/ (or ddxroot.Path()/plugins/\u003cname\u003e/ in convention mode) if present.\n   - ${XDG_DATA_HOME}/ddx/global/plugins/\u003cname\u003e/ otherwise.\n   - Hardcoded baked-in fallback (the default ddx plugin only).\n\n6. The \"ddx-validate\" pre-commit hook (per ddx-777f4a09 already landed) must continue to scope its checks correctly: skill-related validation runs only when skill files are staged, regardless of install location.\n\n7. `ddx doctor` reports both install layers: \"Global Install (${XDG_DATA_HOME}/ddx/global/plugins/ddx) — ok | missing\" and \"Project Install (ddxroot.Path()/plugins/ddx) — ok | missing | lazy-resolves-to-global\".\n\nSPEC IMPACT (in addition to ddx-06cbaa90's spec updates):\n- docs/helix/02-design/adr/ADR-025-or-equivalent (skill install topology) — file or update.\n- library/skills/ddx/SKILL.md \"How this skill works\" section — document install locations.\n- library/skills/ddx/reference/agents.md (if exists) — document agent-tier paths.\n- CLAUDE.md \"Persona System\" section — document install precedence.\n\nNON-SCOPE\n- Removing the existing per-project install entirely (both modes coexist).\n- Migrating ~/.config/ddx/ legacy paths if any exist (likely none today).\n- Agent-harness path discovery beyond Claude Code and Codex (add others as those harnesses define their skill paths).\n\nDEPS\nddx-06cbaa90 (ddx home resolution) — install paths route through ddxroot.Path() AND the new ${XDG_DATA_HOME}/ddx/global/ path. Both must be agreed-on before this lands.","events":[{"actor":"ddx","body":"{\"resolved_provider\":\"claude\",\"resolved_model\":\"opus\",\"fallback_chain\":[]}","created_at":"2026-06-02T01:48:17.508736688Z","kind":"routing","source":"legacy agent execute-bead","summary":"provider=claude model=opus"},{"actor":"ddx","body":"{\"attempt_id\":\"20260602T014107-0c79f3d8\",\"harness\":\"claude\",\"model\":\"opus\",\"input_tokens\":4310,\"output_tokens\":27788,\"total_tokens\":32098,\"cost_usd\":2.1671485,\"duration_ms\":423944,\"exit_code\":0}","created_at":"2026-06-02T01:48:17.559152643Z","kind":"cost","source":"legacy agent execute-bead","summary":"tokens=32098 cost_usd=2.1671 model=opus"},{"actor":"ddx","body":"{\"actual_harness\":\"claude\",\"actual_model\":\"opus\",\"actual_power\":0,\"actual_provider\":\"\",\"attempt_id\":\"20260602T014107-0c79f3d8\",\"bead_id\":\"ddx-937de9fc\",\"estimated_difficulty\":\"hard\",\"rejected_route_pins\":null,\"requested_power_class\":\"smart\",\"requested_profile\":\"smart\",\"routing_intent_degraded\":false,\"routing_intent_note\":\"\",\"routing_intent_source\":\"readiness\"}","created_at":"2026-06-02T01:48:19.256074063Z","kind":"execution-routing-intent","source":"ddx work","summary":"source=readiness difficulty=hard powerClass=smart model=opus harness=claude"},{"actor":"erik","body":"{\"ac_map\":[{\"parent_ac\":\"1. `ddx install \\u003cname\\u003e --global --silent` installs the plugin to ${XDG_DATA_HOME}/ddx/global/plugins/\\u003cname\\u003e/ and creates a symlink or copy under ~/.claude/skills/\\u003cname\\u003e and ~/.agents/skills/\\u003cname\\u003e.\",\"coverage\":\"install/update bead AC 1 (TestInstallGlobal_WritesXDGAndAgentTierLinks)\"},{\"parent_ac\":\"2. `ddx install \\u003cname\\u003e` (no --global, in-tree mode) installs to \\u003cproject\\u003e/.ddx/plugins/\\u003cname\\u003e/ and creates project-tier links under \\u003cproject\\u003e/.claude/skills/\\u003cname\\u003e and \\u003cproject\\u003e/.agents/skills/\\u003cname\\u003e.\",\"coverage\":\"install/update bead AC 2 (TestInstallProject_InTreeLinks)\"},{\"parent_ac\":\"3. `ddx install \\u003cname\\u003e` (no --global, convention mode) installs to ${XDG_DATA_HOME}/ddx/projects/\\u003chost\\u003e/\\u003cowner\\u003e/\\u003crepo\\u003e/plugins/\\u003cname\\u003e/ and creates project-tier links pointing into that XDG plugins/ path.\",\"coverage\":\"install/update bead AC 3 (TestInstallProject_ConventionLinks)\"},{\"parent_ac\":\"4. TestPluginLookup_PrefersProjectOverGlobal asserts that when both paths have the plugin, the project copy wins.\",\"coverage\":\"registry-resolver bead AC 2 (TestPluginLookup_PrefersProjectOverGlobal)\"},{\"parent_ac\":\"5. TestPluginLookup_FallsBackToGlobal asser